1
00:00:07,092 --> 00:00:09,068
We need to land the car.

2
00:00:09,068 --> 00:00:11,404
[Benefit Round Four]
This is killing me.

3
00:00:11,404 --> 00:00:12,472
[Will it work this time?]

4
00:00:12,472 --> 00:00:14,407
Please don't be another phone...

5
00:00:14,407 --> 00:00:16,026
[Third phone in a row]

6
00:00:16,026 --> 00:00:17,743
Maybe yesterday's leftover cash can save...

7
00:00:17,743 --> 00:00:18,850
One more shot at this?

8
00:00:18,850 --> 00:00:20,030
[Pay to retry?]
You mean with 65,000 won?

9
00:00:20,030 --> 00:00:21,630
Count me in, totally in.

10
00:00:21,630 --> 00:00:23,816
[A second chance for everything]
No hard feelings, promise.

11
00:00:23,816 --> 00:00:25,218
[Picked one!]

12
00:00:25,218 --> 00:00:27,119
[Vehicle]
Show me a bit more.

13
00:00:27,119 --> 00:00:29,460
[Vehicle won!]

14
00:00:29,460 --> 00:00:30,957
Alright, so what's next?

15
00:00:30,957 --> 00:00:32,058
Jeju, here we come.

16
00:00:32,058 --> 00:00:34,117
[First stop with the dream car...]
Feels like a storm just blew through.

17
00:00:34,117 --> 00:00:35,734
Hey, get in line.

18
00:00:35,734 --> 00:00:37,597
[First in line for Tto* Bakery's opening]
That bread smell is killer.

19
00:00:37,597 --> 00:00:39,608
[Picking with care]

20
00:00:39,608 --> 00:00:41,901
Never had bread this fresh
from the oven before.

21
00:00:41,901 --> 00:00:43,626
[Mmm]

22
00:00:43,626 --> 00:00:45,171
[Hooked on the taste, driving full speed...]
This is unreal.

23
00:00:45,171 --> 00:00:47,440
[Arrived at Wando Port]
We really made it all the way down.

24
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:49,977
[Boarding the ferry to Jeju]
- This thing is huge. - So massive.

25
00:00:49,977 --> 00:00:52,437
A cup of coffee would save my life.
I'm wiped out right now.

26
00:00:52,437 --> 00:00:55,696
Nail the exact time and three cups are yours.

27
00:00:55,696 --> 00:00:57,037
It is 3:35.

28
00:00:57,037 --> 00:00:58,259
That's correct.

29
00:00:58,259 --> 00:01:00,293
- No way, show me!
- Seriously?

30
00:01:00,293 --> 00:01:02,355
[Spot-on answer shakes the ferry]
What just happened!

31
00:01:02,355 --> 00:01:03,726
[Finally, one drink per person]

32
00:01:03,726 --> 00:01:05,458
This feels like my first real cup of coffee.

33
00:01:05,458 --> 00:01:07,635
Since this whole trip started.

34
00:01:07,635 --> 00:01:08,794
What time is it now?

35
00:01:08,794 --> 00:01:09,696
[4:30 PM, ferry to Jeju]
It's four thirty.

36
00:01:09,696 --> 00:01:11,797
- An hour left to go.
- Just an hour?

37
00:01:11,797 --> 00:01:13,490
Should we check out the deck
real quick before crashing?

38
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:14,567
- Let's go check the deck.
- Yeah.

39
00:01:14,567 --> 00:01:17,102
[Deck first, then sleep]
Quick peek up there, then crash.

40
00:01:18,959 --> 00:01:20,526
That was such a blast.

41
00:01:20,526 --> 00:01:22,942
Time just flew by.

42
00:01:22,942 --> 00:01:25,344
[Riding the high of the time-guessing game]

43
00:01:25,344 --> 00:01:29,272
[Heading up to the deck]

44
00:01:31,951 --> 00:01:34,020
[Jaw-dropping the second they see it]

45
00:01:34,020 --> 00:01:37,376
[Ocean stretching forever]

46
00:01:37,376 --> 00:01:39,476
It's nothing but ocean out here.

47
00:01:39,476 --> 00:01:41,426
Check out that view.

48
00:01:43,362 --> 00:01:45,193
[They step closer to the sea]

49
00:01:45,193 --> 00:01:47,256
- That's pretty fast.
- Yeah.

50
00:01:47,256 --> 00:01:49,377
People feed seagulls shrimp crackers, right?

51
00:01:49,377 --> 00:01:51,436
They snatch it midair.

52
00:01:51,436 --> 00:01:52,672
[Slides in]
Just watch that.

53
00:01:52,672 --> 00:01:54,507
[Air shrimp crackers]

54
00:01:54,507 --> 00:01:57,478
[Saving every won, even on snacks...]

55
00:01:58,110 --> 00:02:00,713
The seagulls are actually keeping up.

56
00:02:00,713 --> 00:02:02,715
[Sorry, seagulls]

57
00:02:02,715 --> 00:02:05,051
[Camcorder comes out at every pretty spot]

58
00:02:05,051 --> 00:02:06,052
[Say hi]

59
00:02:06,052 --> 00:02:07,153
[Wave]

60
00:02:07,153 --> 00:02:11,379
[Just a wave makes it
look like a coming-of-age movie]

61
00:02:11,379 --> 00:02:13,593
That camera's basically stuck on just us two.

62
00:02:13,593 --> 00:02:14,637
[Hahaha]

63
00:02:14,637 --> 00:02:16,329
My turn to film.

64
00:02:16,329 --> 00:02:19,834
[Walks over and grabs the camcorder]

65
00:02:22,101 --> 00:02:23,819
[#Jeju-bound from Wando]
[Starting with inserts]

66
00:02:25,193 --> 00:02:27,540
[Capturing Yumi and Woo Shik too]
Hey, that guy's actually feeding them.

67
00:02:27,540 --> 00:02:29,475
[Peace]

68
00:02:29,475 --> 00:02:34,412
[Happiness MAX]

69
00:02:34,412 --> 00:02:35,780
Want me to grab a photo for you?

70
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:37,717
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

71
00:02:37,717 --> 00:02:40,720
[The three huddle right up]

72
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:46,726
[So many rules, yet weirdly romantic]

73
00:02:49,395 --> 00:02:52,331
[Memory captured with the blue sea behind them]

74
00:02:52,331 --> 00:02:54,560
[Done admiring the sea]

75
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,335
Hey there.

76
00:02:56,335 --> 00:03:00,005
[Time to rest up]

77
00:03:02,642 --> 00:03:05,410
[What's everyone doing?]

78
00:03:06,545 --> 00:03:08,359
[Just back from the deck]

79
00:03:08,359 --> 00:03:10,393
Want to play something?

80
00:03:10,393 --> 00:03:11,384
A game, maybe?

81
00:03:11,384 --> 00:03:13,148
[Bored stiff, the three of them...]

82
00:03:13,148 --> 00:03:15,021
How about Mafia, you guys in?

83
00:03:15,021 --> 00:03:16,995
[Pitching Mafia to the crew]
Not a bad idea.

84
00:03:16,995 --> 00:03:18,259
- Honestly.
- You serious?

85
00:03:18,259 --> 00:03:20,015
- Seriously.
- That sounds fun.

86
00:03:20,015 --> 00:03:21,027
- For real?
- For real.

87
00:03:21,027 --> 00:03:22,059
Let's do it.

88
00:03:22,059 --> 00:03:23,395
Mafia is my absolute favorite.

89
00:03:23,395 --> 00:03:25,831
I love this game. I'm so down for this.

90
00:03:25,831 --> 00:03:29,159
[Three actors way too into it...]
My heart's actually pounding.

91
00:03:29,159 --> 00:03:31,070
You're the Mafia, aren't you?

92
00:03:31,070 --> 00:03:32,159
[Mafia game ready to roll]

93
00:03:32,159 --> 00:03:33,639
Morning has come.

94
00:03:33,639 --> 00:03:35,908
[Unplanned Trip Ferry Mafia]
[Nine players total, four different roles]

95
00:03:35,908 --> 00:03:36,976
[Three Mafia]

96
00:03:36,976 --> 00:03:38,978
[One cop, one doctor, four citizens]

97
00:03:38,978 --> 00:03:43,215
[Citizens win by eliminating all Mafia]

98
00:03:43,215 --> 00:03:45,929
[Viewers, play along too]

99
00:03:45,929 --> 00:03:47,369
[Day 1 kicks off with intros]
Let's go around and introduce ourselves.

100
00:03:47,369 --> 00:03:48,929
I'm just a citizen.

101
00:03:48,929 --> 00:03:50,410
Citizen here too.

102
00:03:50,410 --> 00:03:52,169
I'm an upstanding citizen.

103
00:03:52,169 --> 00:03:53,429
[The citizen chain keeps going]
Same here, citizen.

104
00:03:53,429 --> 00:03:54,290
[Citizens 12345]
Also a citizen.

105
00:03:54,290 --> 00:03:55,361
Just an ordinary citizen.

106
00:03:55,361 --> 00:03:57,059
I'm a brave citizen.

107
00:03:57,059 --> 00:03:58,164
[Well...]

108
00:03:58,164 --> 00:04:01,734
The name's Frank,
I work over at the dairy farm.

109
00:04:01,734 --> 00:04:04,030
[Frank, 36, Dairy Farm Worker]

110
00:04:05,204 --> 00:04:06,893
I'm the cop.

111
00:04:06,893 --> 00:04:09,275
- Huh?
- What?

112
00:04:09,275 --> 00:04:10,526
[Yumi, the only one revealing her role]

113
00:04:10,526 --> 00:04:12,827
- You're not supposed to say it.
- She's totally Mafia.

114
00:04:12,827 --> 00:04:14,370
No, I'm not Mafia, I swear.

115
00:04:14,370 --> 00:04:16,048
This guy's got to be Mafia.

116
00:04:16,048 --> 00:04:17,717
How come?

117
00:04:17,717 --> 00:04:19,092
[Attempt 1: Yumi pinning it on Woo Shik]

118
00:04:19,092 --> 00:04:21,423
- For real.
- He just said he works at a dairy farm.

119
00:04:21,423 --> 00:04:24,126
Frank from the dairy farm, what's the issue?

120
00:04:24,126 --> 00:04:26,346
The cop can check at night, you know.

121
00:04:26,346 --> 00:04:28,272
[The cop picks one player each night to ID]

122
00:04:30,262 --> 00:04:33,332
[Attempt 2: Yumi points at the director across]

123
00:04:33,332 --> 00:04:37,136
[He does look kind of jumpy]

124
00:04:37,136 --> 00:04:39,660
He just shot her a glare a second ago.

125
00:04:39,660 --> 00:04:42,303
[Did Yumi's pitch land?]
For starters, please point out

126
00:04:42,303 --> 00:04:46,712
[Day 1 Voting]
who you think the Mafia is. One, two, three.

127
00:04:46,712 --> 00:04:48,781
[Six votes, one vote, one vote]

128
00:04:48,781 --> 00:04:50,021
[Seven votes]

129
00:04:50,021 --> 00:04:52,818
One person's getting all the votes here.

130
00:04:52,818 --> 00:04:56,193
[Maybe thanks to Yumi, swamped with votes...]
You get ten seconds for your final words.

131
00:04:56,193 --> 00:04:57,323
Well...

132
00:04:57,323 --> 00:04:59,126
The vote's about to happen...

133
00:04:59,126 --> 00:05:00,493
But you guys need to keep me alive.

134
00:05:00,493 --> 00:05:01,626
[The room stirs]
- What? - Huh?

135
00:05:01,626 --> 00:05:02,742
What's the reason though?

136
00:05:02,742 --> 00:05:04,096
You've got to keep me alive

137
00:05:04,096 --> 00:05:06,460
so the citizens can all survive.

138
00:05:06,460 --> 00:05:07,867
[Frank, impressed]
Alright, from this point on,

139
00:05:07,867 --> 00:05:11,137
[Day 1 Vote]
we'll go with majority rules.

140
00:05:11,137 --> 00:05:13,226
- Spare him.
- Me too.

141
00:05:13,226 --> 00:05:15,159
- Five votes to spare.
- Read the room, people.

142
00:05:15,159 --> 00:05:17,626
[Spare, Five] [Eliminate, Three]
He lives, then.

143
00:05:17,626 --> 00:05:19,645
Night falls again.

144
00:05:19,645 --> 00:05:21,213
[First night arrives with no casualties]

145
00:05:21,213 --> 00:05:22,726
[Wonder what went down overnight?]

146
00:05:22,726 --> 00:05:24,905
Morning has arrived.

147
00:05:24,905 --> 00:05:26,959
[As Day 2 begins]
Overnight,

148
00:05:26,959 --> 00:05:30,589
[News of a death rolls in]
we lost one player.

149
00:05:30,589 --> 00:05:31,824
The victim is...

150
00:05:31,824 --> 00:05:33,660
[First down, Po-po?]

151
00:05:33,660 --> 00:05:35,359
From this point on,

152
00:05:35,359 --> 00:05:37,460
[So she wasn't Mafia after all]
no words

153
00:05:37,460 --> 00:05:39,265
[Wait, me? Why me...]
from your end.

154
00:05:39,265 --> 00:05:41,526
[Why though?]
Step back a tiny bit, please.

155
00:05:41,526 --> 00:05:42,646
[Why?]
Zip those lips.

156
00:05:42,646 --> 00:05:43,836
You're not allowed.

157
00:05:43,836 --> 00:05:45,708
[Speech rights gone in five minutes flat]

158
00:05:45,708 --> 00:05:49,175
She got iced for saying she was the cop.

159
00:05:49,175 --> 00:05:51,621
[Yumi didn't know, going wild Day 1
means lights out]

160
00:05:51,621 --> 00:05:54,159
Somebody during the night

161
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:55,689
[So unfair]
took her down,

162
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:58,229
- I mean, why on earth...
- and the doctor failed to save this player.

163
00:05:58,229 --> 00:05:59,878
Turns out Yumi

164
00:05:59,878 --> 00:06:01,187
was a citizen.

165
00:06:01,187 --> 00:06:02,087
And then...

166
00:06:02,087 --> 00:06:03,489
[Pfft]

167
00:06:03,489 --> 00:06:05,624
The second thing kicked off...

168
00:06:05,624 --> 00:06:07,026
[Q. What were you thinking?]

169
00:06:07,026 --> 00:06:10,196
The Mafia rules I knew were totally different.

170
00:06:10,196 --> 00:06:15,000
Host, Mafia, citizens,
that's the only version I'd done.

171
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,927
Roles with jobs were brand new to me.

172
00:06:16,927 --> 00:06:18,436
Guess that's why I went down fast.

173
00:06:18,436 --> 00:06:21,516
Saying citizen no matter what
never crossed my mind.

174
00:06:21,516 --> 00:06:23,909
Thought I was throwing them off.

175
00:06:23,909 --> 00:06:27,413
All I did was introduce myself. Why kill me?

176
00:06:27,413 --> 00:06:29,226
[Po-po taking a break]

177
00:06:29,226 --> 00:06:30,249
- Three of them, right?
- Yeah.

178
00:06:30,249 --> 00:06:31,460
[Day 2 Discussion Begins]
Three Mafia.

179
00:06:31,460 --> 00:06:33,886
The PD though, she's kind of...

180
00:06:33,886 --> 00:06:36,155
- Her face went all stiff.
- Totally.

181
00:06:36,155 --> 00:06:38,026
[What?]

182
00:06:38,026 --> 00:06:40,326
[Pinning it on the person next to her]
She had this look at me, like this.

183
00:06:40,326 --> 00:06:42,533
- It wasn't like that.
- Her usual vibe and style.

184
00:06:42,533 --> 00:06:43,853
You guys know her, don't you?

185
00:06:43,853 --> 00:06:45,898
The Yu Jin PD I know,

186
00:06:45,898 --> 00:06:47,616
if somebody called her Mafia like this,

187
00:06:47,616 --> 00:06:48,760
- "That's not it."
- she would jump right in

188
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,770
- Right.
- and say "here's why it's not me."

189
00:06:50,770 --> 00:06:52,872
- That's what she'd do, but now...
- Yeah...

190
00:06:52,872 --> 00:06:55,560
[Gotcha]

191
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:57,576
Something's off.

192
00:06:58,852 --> 00:07:00,733
Had no clue people were pointing fingers at me.

193
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:02,415
- Huh?
- No?

194
00:07:02,415 --> 00:07:04,350
She looks pretty thrown right now.

195
00:07:04,350 --> 00:07:05,951
[Highly suspicious]

196
00:07:05,951 --> 00:07:07,353
[Day 2 Voting]
Let's just vote at this point.

197
00:07:07,353 --> 00:07:09,593
- Yeah.
- The vibe's there, go ahead.

198
00:07:09,593 --> 00:07:12,124
Vote on one, two, three.

199
00:07:12,124 --> 00:07:14,710
[Two votes, four votes, one vote, one vote]
She's pulling in the most votes here.

200
00:07:14,710 --> 00:07:15,989
The look in her eyes...

201
00:07:15,989 --> 00:07:18,909
Yu Jin PD, you've got ten seconds
for last words.

202
00:07:18,909 --> 00:07:20,670
This is so beyond unfair, honestly.

203
00:07:20,670 --> 00:07:22,534
[Hands clasped tight]
Seriously, I'm not the Mafia.

204
00:07:22,534 --> 00:07:24,904
[Couldn't hold the laugh]

205
00:07:24,904 --> 00:07:27,440
[Just trust me, okay...]

206
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:30,147
[Day 2 Vote]
One, two, three.

207
00:07:30,147 --> 00:07:32,144
[Spare, Two] [Eliminate, Five]
By a landslide,

208
00:07:32,144 --> 00:07:35,092
Yu Jin PD has been eliminated.

209
00:07:35,092 --> 00:07:37,493
[Self moment of silence]
Over to the dead zone.

210
00:07:37,493 --> 00:07:39,092
Yu Jin PD

211
00:07:39,092 --> 00:07:40,819
turned out to be Mafia.

212
00:07:40,819 --> 00:07:43,523
[First Mafia caught]

213
00:07:43,523 --> 00:07:44,719
[Welcome]
Mafia.

214
00:07:44,719 --> 00:07:46,008
Alright, night falls.

215
00:07:46,008 --> 00:07:47,693
Night falls.

216
00:07:47,693 --> 00:07:48,928
Night is here.

217
00:07:48,928 --> 00:07:50,593
[Time to reveal the roles]

218
00:07:50,593 --> 00:07:52,526
Cop, raise your head quietly

219
00:07:52,526 --> 00:07:53,899
[Cop: Writer Sae Byeol]
and point at someone.

220
00:07:53,899 --> 00:07:56,159
Next, doctor, quietly raise your head

221
00:07:56,159 --> 00:07:58,257
[Doctor: Seo Jun]
and pick someone to save.

222
00:07:58,257 --> 00:08:01,473
Mafia, raise your heads quietly

223
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:04,977
[Mafia: Woo Shik]
and show me who dies.

224
00:08:04,977 --> 00:08:07,013
[Director Deok Hwan]

225
00:08:07,013 --> 00:08:09,048
Morning has arrived.

226
00:08:09,048 --> 00:08:11,256
[Day 3 morning rolls in]

227
00:08:11,256 --> 00:08:14,159
A good, honest citizen

228
00:08:14,159 --> 00:08:16,593
has been killed.

229
00:08:16,593 --> 00:08:18,256
Who is it?

230
00:08:18,958 --> 00:08:21,059
[Doctor fails to save a citizen again]
[Doctor]

231
00:08:21,059 --> 00:08:22,762
So he was really a citizen?

232
00:08:22,762 --> 00:08:23,862
[Four Citizens : Two Mafia]

233
00:08:23,862 --> 00:08:25,460
Hold up.

234
00:08:25,460 --> 00:08:27,933
- Wait a sec.
- Where's this coming from?

235
00:08:27,933 --> 00:08:29,043
[Pointing at Deok Hwan]
Mafia.

236
00:08:29,043 --> 00:08:30,836
- That's not me.
- No really, Mafia for sure.

237
00:08:30,836 --> 00:08:33,238
[Cop targets Deok Hwan right off the bat]
- Not true. - Here's my read.

238
00:08:33,238 --> 00:08:35,274
[Earlier that night]
Cop, raise your head quietly

239
00:08:35,274 --> 00:08:36,608
and make your pick.

240
00:08:36,608 --> 00:08:38,177
[Cop points at him]

241
00:08:38,177 --> 00:08:40,827
[Nailed the Mafia ID]

242
00:08:40,827 --> 00:08:42,348
So that leaves us with...

243
00:08:42,348 --> 00:08:43,935
[Cop pushes the Mafia case with confidence]

244
00:08:43,935 --> 00:08:46,385
- Right, this guy.
- Yeah.

245
00:08:46,385 --> 00:08:47,653
That's it.

246
00:08:47,653 --> 00:08:49,822
[Woo Shik the Mafia goes along for now]

247
00:08:49,822 --> 00:08:50,726
[Rub]

248
00:08:50,726 --> 00:08:53,392
- We're playing Mafia and...
- He's wiping sweat right now.

249
00:08:53,392 --> 00:08:55,893
[Sweat in suspicious places]
- Sweat pooling above his lip. - This is...

250
00:08:55,893 --> 00:08:57,193
Guess it suddenly got warm in here.

251
00:08:57,193 --> 00:08:59,132
Nope.

252
00:08:59,132 --> 00:09:01,326
I'm telling you, it's him.

253
00:09:01,326 --> 00:09:03,603
[Meanwhile Woo Shik's words dry up...]
Since he is dead...

254
00:09:03,603 --> 00:09:05,493
And as for me,

255
00:09:05,493 --> 00:09:08,022
he gives off a fishy vibe too.

256
00:09:08,022 --> 00:09:09,975
- Me?
- You're acting off right now.

257
00:09:09,975 --> 00:09:12,783
No, that's not it.

258
00:09:12,783 --> 00:09:15,147
See, over at the milk plant these days,

259
00:09:15,147 --> 00:09:17,249
I'm pulling five days a week there,

260
00:09:17,249 --> 00:09:19,268
so no Mafia cartel ever fits my schedule.

261
00:09:19,268 --> 00:09:21,363
Getting that milk out fast is all I care about.

262
00:09:21,363 --> 00:09:23,463
If a real doctor's here, throw me one save.

263
00:09:23,463 --> 00:09:24,693
Just for now, what if...

264
00:09:24,693 --> 00:09:26,392
Huh?

265
00:09:26,392 --> 00:09:28,060
[Two Mafia point at the cop at once?]

266
00:09:28,060 --> 00:09:29,660
Why pile on like that?

267
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:32,457
- Hold on...
- Where's this coming from?

268
00:09:32,457 --> 00:09:36,001
Leave my name out of it.

269
00:09:36,001 --> 00:09:38,078
- Quit dragging me in.
- The Mafia is splitting apart.

270
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:39,798
They're turning on each other now.

271
00:09:39,798 --> 00:09:41,398
[Day 3 nomination]
Time to call out a name.

272
00:09:41,398 --> 00:09:43,618
Point to whoever looks shadiest.

273
00:09:43,618 --> 00:09:45,844
On three, here we go.

274
00:09:45,844 --> 00:09:47,359
[One vote, two votes, three votes]

275
00:09:47,359 --> 00:09:50,018
[The Director's caught]
Three votes land right here, the top count.

276
00:09:50,018 --> 00:09:52,618
[Day 3 vote]
Vote to spare him or take him out.

277
00:09:52,618 --> 00:09:54,486
Ready, set, now.

278
00:09:54,486 --> 00:09:57,126
[Spare, One : Eliminate, Four]
I'm voting to execute.

279
00:09:57,126 --> 00:09:59,024
[Saved his own teammate by mistake]
I'm voting to execute.

280
00:09:59,825 --> 00:10:01,561
[Oh no...]

281
00:10:01,561 --> 00:10:03,561
Hold up.

282
00:10:04,326 --> 00:10:07,294
[Frank just made a fatal blunder]
Time out.

283
00:10:07,294 --> 00:10:09,535
[Just get over here]
I mean it.

284
00:10:09,535 --> 00:10:11,304
Director Deok Hwan didn't make it,

285
00:10:11,304 --> 00:10:12,927
and the role he was hiding

286
00:10:12,927 --> 00:10:14,773
turns out to be Mafia.

287
00:10:15,541 --> 00:10:18,526
[No argument there]

288
00:10:18,526 --> 00:10:20,159
That's a wrap.

289
00:10:20,159 --> 00:10:21,293
[A new day breaks]
Down to four players now.

290
00:10:21,293 --> 00:10:23,259
[Four remaining]
So the prime suspect right now,

291
00:10:23,259 --> 00:10:26,193
[Citizen, Mafia, Doctor, Citizen]
- Look. - it's so plain...

292
00:10:26,193 --> 00:10:30,359
The Mafia already locked onto me.

293
00:10:30,359 --> 00:10:32,858
They're pinning the Mafia label on me,

294
00:10:32,858 --> 00:10:33,859
steering it that way.

295
00:10:33,859 --> 00:10:34,939
Didn't I bring this up before?

296
00:10:34,939 --> 00:10:38,118
[A heated closing plea]
One of these two is who I'm zeroing in on.

297
00:10:38,118 --> 00:10:39,860
So how about it? Out on the field,

298
00:10:39,860 --> 00:10:41,839
playing soccer solo with no team behind you?

299
00:10:41,839 --> 00:10:43,626
Pretty rough, yeah.

300
00:10:43,626 --> 00:10:45,871
[Why even ask, man...]

301
00:10:45,871 --> 00:10:48,173
[Bittersweet pal 1, bittersweet pal 2]

302
00:10:48,173 --> 00:10:50,059
[Final nomination]
Let's run the last vote.

303
00:10:50,059 --> 00:10:51,610
After making it all this way...

304
00:10:51,610 --> 00:10:53,912
- What a shame.
- You're all on the same page, right?

305
00:10:53,912 --> 00:10:55,613
- One, two, three.
- For real.

306
00:10:55,613 --> 00:10:56,628
[Landslide vote]

307
00:10:56,628 --> 00:10:59,279
[Thumbs up till the end]

308
00:10:59,279 --> 00:11:00,740
[Closing plea]
We really came this far together.

309
00:11:00,740 --> 00:11:02,793
If I go down here, the Mafia

310
00:11:02,793 --> 00:11:04,500
get exactly the picture they wanted.

311
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:06,391
[Final vote]
Two, three.

312
00:11:06,391 --> 00:11:08,281
[Spare, One : Eliminate, Three]

313
00:11:09,959 --> 00:11:12,239
If he's not Mafia, then I'm lost here.

314
00:11:12,239 --> 00:11:13,400
As for Choi Woo Shik...

315
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:17,460
If I'm not the Mafia, then it's over.

316
00:11:17,460 --> 00:11:19,359
He's the Mafia.

317
00:11:19,359 --> 00:11:20,439
[Good Game]

318
00:11:20,439 --> 00:11:21,899
[Slipping away]

319
00:11:21,899 --> 00:11:24,626
The Citizens take it.

320
00:11:24,626 --> 00:11:27,412
- They're so good at this.
- The writer right here was the cop.

321
00:11:27,412 --> 00:11:29,948
[Time now 5:40 PM]
So she was the cop.

322
00:11:29,948 --> 00:11:32,226
[The wild Mafia wraps,
and Jeju sits right ahead]

323
00:11:32,226 --> 00:11:34,226
There's Jeju up ahead now.

324
00:11:34,226 --> 00:11:36,246
The Jeju we kept dreaming of.

325
00:11:36,246 --> 00:11:39,307
[Hearts race as Jeju nears]
What kind of fun adventures are waiting for us?

326
00:11:39,307 --> 00:11:40,447
So what's the plan for real?

327
00:11:40,447 --> 00:11:41,727
Do we hit the room first,

328
00:11:41,727 --> 00:11:43,126
or should the BBQ spot come first?

329
00:11:43,126 --> 00:11:44,567
[Scrambling to make a plan]
The room...

330
00:11:44,567 --> 00:11:46,407
Let's head toward Ilchulbong for now.

331
00:11:46,407 --> 00:11:47,386
- Should we?
- Yeah.

332
00:11:47,386 --> 00:11:49,127
Dinner tonight is going to be amazing.

333
00:11:49,127 --> 00:11:51,506
You've got to try that place.
It's seriously good.

334
00:11:51,506 --> 00:11:55,007
I've never had an experience like this.

335
00:11:55,007 --> 00:11:56,676
I'll take the wheel from here.

336
00:11:56,676 --> 00:11:58,409
[5:56 PM, Jeju Port]
Sure.

337
00:11:59,793 --> 00:12:00,879
We're in Jeju!

338
00:12:00,879 --> 00:12:01,952
Where are we?

339
00:12:01,952 --> 00:12:04,760
This is Jeju Port.

340
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,385
We actually made it.

341
00:12:06,385 --> 00:12:07,293
Yeah!

342
00:12:07,293 --> 00:12:09,320
Jeju, baby!

343
00:12:10,593 --> 00:12:14,326
- I wanted to come to Jeju so bad.
- We really did land in Jeju.

344
00:12:14,326 --> 00:12:16,028
Is this for real?

345
00:12:16,028 --> 00:12:17,991
[Still surreal]
No really, is this happening?

346
00:12:17,991 --> 00:12:20,165
I think I've still got my youth in me.

347
00:12:20,165 --> 00:12:21,699
Yeah, I'm young at heart.

348
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:23,789
[You're watching Unplanned Trip]
25.

349
00:12:23,789 --> 00:12:26,599
Huh? Seongsan Ilchulbong...

350
00:12:26,599 --> 00:12:28,519
- Let's plug this in first.
- Okay.

351
00:12:28,519 --> 00:12:30,370
Try typing in that whole thing once.

352
00:12:30,370 --> 00:12:32,744
- What was it again?
- It started with "Jeil..."

353
00:12:32,744 --> 00:12:34,560
[The second they get in,
here's what they search the GPS for]

354
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:37,149
There's a black pork spot
a security guy told me about.

355
00:12:37,149 --> 00:12:39,770
Whenever I'm in Jeju lately,
I always end up there.

356
00:12:39,770 --> 00:12:41,420
[A black pork joint they often hit]
And there's just that one restaurant

357
00:12:41,420 --> 00:12:43,089
sitting by the shore.

358
00:12:43,089 --> 00:12:44,022
Go!

359
00:12:44,022 --> 00:12:45,724
[Ep. 5: a phone lifeline for the name, but...]

360
00:12:45,724 --> 00:12:48,093
<i>That "top-quality black pork place."</i>

361
00:12:48,093 --> 00:12:50,259
- "Top grade?"
- Hang it up.

362
00:12:50,259 --> 00:12:51,370
[Lifeline over]
Hang up.

363
00:12:51,370 --> 00:12:54,641
Why are you talking so loudly?

364
00:12:55,321 --> 00:12:56,927
[Speechless]

365
00:12:56,927 --> 00:12:59,204
Did he say "ilgeun?"

366
00:12:59,204 --> 00:13:00,973
I think he said "ilgeum."

367
00:13:00,973 --> 00:13:02,175
Wasn't it "ilgeup?" Top grade?

368
00:13:02,175 --> 00:13:04,676
[Not a single person heard it properly...]
"Jeil Top Grade Black Pork."

369
00:13:04,676 --> 00:13:08,013
Let's just type "Seongsan Ilchulbong Jeil"
into the GPS for now.

370
00:13:08,013 --> 00:13:09,760
[Leaving the rest to the GPS]
- Right? That'll do it. - Yeah.

371
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:10,983
- A bunch of them should pop up.
- They will, right?

372
00:13:10,983 --> 00:13:12,626
Yeah, I bet they show.

373
00:13:12,626 --> 00:13:13,686
"Il..."

374
00:13:13,686 --> 00:13:16,259
- "Ilgeup?"
- Try "ilgeum," type "ilgeum."

375
00:13:16,259 --> 00:13:18,226
"Black pork..."

376
00:13:18,226 --> 00:13:20,022
Nothing.

377
00:13:20,022 --> 00:13:21,660
So I'm guessing

378
00:13:21,660 --> 00:13:24,363
what he said after that was the right one.

379
00:13:24,363 --> 00:13:26,827
If it's not here, we won't track it down.

380
00:13:26,827 --> 00:13:28,663
I think I saw "Jeil," actually.

381
00:13:28,663 --> 00:13:30,243
- Same here.
- I caught it too.

382
00:13:30,243 --> 00:13:31,370
Scroll down a bit.

383
00:13:31,370 --> 00:13:32,660
[The "Jeil" from the call was right there...]

384
00:13:32,660 --> 00:13:35,722
- "Yeoljeong..."
- It wasn't a place like this.

385
00:13:35,722 --> 00:13:37,602
It should be somewhere like this.

386
00:13:37,602 --> 00:13:40,212
Somewhere like this, this kind of spot.

387
00:13:40,212 --> 00:13:42,515
Right? It's down by the shore, around here.

388
00:13:42,515 --> 00:13:45,117
It sat right up on that hill.

389
00:13:45,117 --> 00:13:47,619
[Jeju's coastal hills number
in the tens of thousands]

390
00:13:47,619 --> 00:13:49,421
[Hmm... let me think...]

391
00:13:49,421 --> 00:13:52,024
I think looking for it in person
is the smarter move.

392
00:13:52,024 --> 00:13:53,827
Going at it this way is endless.

393
00:13:53,827 --> 00:13:57,947
But how do we even ask people about it?

394
00:13:57,947 --> 00:14:00,332
Is there anywhere to get on a PC?

395
00:14:00,332 --> 00:14:01,888
Should we just dash to a PC room real quick?

396
00:14:01,888 --> 00:14:03,468
Knock it out in fifteen at the PC room?

397
00:14:03,468 --> 00:14:06,793
Then pull up a nearby PC room on the map.

398
00:14:06,793 --> 00:14:09,147
[Searching right away]
Nearest PC room.

399
00:14:09,147 --> 00:14:10,760
- 800 m.
- 800 m.

400
00:14:10,760 --> 00:14:12,727
- It's right up ahead.
- Hit the PC room,

401
00:14:12,727 --> 00:14:14,568
nail the address down,
in and out in 30 minutes.

402
00:14:14,568 --> 00:14:15,568
That sounds right to me too.

403
00:14:15,568 --> 00:14:16,768
Okay, off to the PC room.

404
00:14:16,768 --> 00:14:18,159
Kim Tae Hyung, Jeju.

405
00:14:18,159 --> 00:14:21,362
- Black pork place should pop right up.
- It'll pop right up.

406
00:14:21,362 --> 00:14:24,756
[Will they really find it that fast?]
Didn't even think of that.

407
00:14:26,858 --> 00:14:29,259
Is the sun coming up right now?

408
00:14:29,259 --> 00:14:30,529
It's magic hour.

409
00:14:30,529 --> 00:14:31,596
So pretty.

410
00:14:31,596 --> 00:14:32,782
[Currently 6:02 PM]
[No, it's actually setting]

411
00:14:32,782 --> 00:14:35,133
This is honestly the prettiest time of day.

412
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:38,337
[Watching from a boat,
but this sunset hits different...]

413
00:14:38,337 --> 00:14:40,203
This is why we came to Jeju.

414
00:14:40,203 --> 00:14:41,883
Jeju's still Jeju after all.

415
00:14:41,883 --> 00:14:43,282
You said it.

416
00:14:43,282 --> 00:14:46,244
It won't be long before that sun's gone.

417
00:14:46,244 --> 00:14:51,901
[But first, the ferry ramp comes down]

418
00:14:51,901 --> 00:14:54,720
- Off we go at last.
- Heading out now.

419
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:57,359
- Let's roll.
- Here we go.

420
00:14:57,359 --> 00:15:00,059
- Weather's perfect right now.
- Yeah.

421
00:15:00,059 --> 00:15:03,195
Can't believe we made it to Jeju by boat.

422
00:15:03,195 --> 00:15:04,904
Yeah!

423
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:07,233
Whoa, gorgeous.

424
00:15:07,233 --> 00:15:10,726
Okay, we need to swing by a PC room real quick.

425
00:15:10,726 --> 00:15:11,793
- Right.
- Got it.

426
00:15:11,793 --> 00:15:13,827
[Oh right, they don't know where to go...]

427
00:15:13,827 --> 00:15:17,002
"Kim Tae Hyung black pork" is way too funny.

428
00:15:17,002 --> 00:15:18,582
- It'll definitely come up.
- Should pop right up.

429
00:15:18,582 --> 00:15:21,079
[Seo Jun, Woo Shik, and Tae Hyung's spot]
Two minutes, easy.

430
00:15:21,079 --> 00:15:24,259
[Then a PC room sign appears in front of them]

431
00:15:24,259 --> 00:15:25,451
[Woo Shik spots it too]

432
00:15:25,451 --> 00:15:26,869
- Looks like this is it.
- This is the place.

433
00:15:26,869 --> 00:15:29,887
But it looks closed.

434
00:15:31,022 --> 00:15:33,729
[Hard to believe this place is open...]
Right?

435
00:15:33,729 --> 00:15:36,269
This one's shut down, doors are closed.

436
00:15:36,269 --> 00:15:38,864
- Not open, huh?
- Sure looks that way.

437
00:15:38,864 --> 00:15:40,798
[Sigh...]

438
00:15:40,798 --> 00:15:42,367
- Doesn't look open.
- Try searching again.

439
00:15:42,367 --> 00:15:43,535
[Forget black pork,
they can't even find a PC room]

440
00:15:43,535 --> 00:15:47,940
[And so they start scouring
all of Jeju City...]

441
00:15:48,869 --> 00:15:50,642
Every PC room around here is closed.

442
00:15:50,642 --> 00:15:52,643
That one's closed too.

443
00:15:53,712 --> 00:15:55,689
[Quick strategy break]

444
00:15:55,689 --> 00:15:58,650
Or we could pop into a 7-Eleven

445
00:15:58,650 --> 00:16:01,712
and ask if someone could
lend us their phone real quick?

446
00:16:01,712 --> 00:16:04,693
Let's just ask to borrow a phone.

447
00:16:04,693 --> 00:16:07,192
- Borrowing a phone might be our only shot.
- Yeah.

448
00:16:07,192 --> 00:16:08,549
There's no other way.

449
00:16:08,549 --> 00:16:09,949
Paris Baguette.

450
00:16:09,949 --> 00:16:12,030
[Target acquired: Paris Baguette]
Paris Baguette.

451
00:16:12,764 --> 00:16:16,889
[Seo Jun steps up on behalf of the trio...]

452
00:16:16,889 --> 00:16:20,071
Man, how do I even ask in here?

453
00:16:20,071 --> 00:16:24,109
[Especially rough for an MBTI introvert...]

454
00:16:24,109 --> 00:16:26,178
[Glances around for no reason...]

455
00:16:26,178 --> 00:16:31,850
[Works up the courage and walks inside]

456
00:16:31,850 --> 00:16:34,152
[More glancing around]

457
00:16:34,152 --> 00:16:36,823
[Grabs a bottle of water for cover]

458
00:16:36,823 --> 00:16:41,126
[Joins the checkout line]

459
00:16:41,126 --> 00:16:43,827
Hi there. Excuse me...

460
00:16:43,827 --> 00:16:47,092
Well... Could I ask you to look something up

461
00:16:47,092 --> 00:16:48,927
on your phone real quick?

462
00:16:48,927 --> 00:16:50,009
Well...

463
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:51,436
[Got the green light to search]

464
00:16:51,436 --> 00:16:55,106
The black pork place

465
00:16:55,106 --> 00:16:57,159
that BTS V went to.

466
00:16:57,159 --> 00:16:59,793
- One second.
- Sure.

467
00:16:59,793 --> 00:17:01,679
Anything coming up?

468
00:17:02,315 --> 00:17:04,049
Could this be it?

469
00:17:04,049 --> 00:17:06,384
[Would that search alone even work?]

470
00:17:06,384 --> 00:17:08,254
This one, no, that's not it.

471
00:17:08,254 --> 00:17:11,303
[Seems there's more than a couple]
He shot a different one here.

472
00:17:11,303 --> 00:17:12,593
This is taking forever.

473
00:17:12,593 --> 00:17:14,304
He should buy some bread
and ask to use their phone.

474
00:17:14,304 --> 00:17:16,363
He should come up right away.

475
00:17:16,363 --> 00:17:20,059
[Trying with a hazy memory of the area]
It's near Seongsan Ilchulbong.

476
00:17:20,059 --> 00:17:21,567
Could it be...

477
00:17:21,567 --> 00:17:23,560
I think this is it.

478
00:17:23,560 --> 00:17:26,442
- Right here.
- Mind if I take a look?

479
00:17:26,442 --> 00:17:29,226
- Could I jot down the address?
- Sure.

480
00:17:29,226 --> 00:17:30,409
[Now let's see...
where can I write this down...]

481
00:17:30,409 --> 00:17:32,956
Hold on, no pen.

482
00:17:32,956 --> 00:17:35,216
Could I borrow this to write it down?

483
00:17:35,216 --> 00:17:37,350
Thanks so much.

484
00:17:37,350 --> 00:17:39,551
- That'll be 1,200 won.
- Okay.

485
00:17:39,551 --> 00:17:40,925
[Fumbling around]

486
00:17:40,925 --> 00:17:42,487
There it is.

487
00:17:42,487 --> 00:17:44,716
Brain's all over the place.

488
00:17:44,716 --> 00:17:46,491
Thank you.

489
00:17:46,491 --> 00:17:47,626
Thanks again.

490
00:17:47,626 --> 00:17:49,995
[Water bottle: -1,200 won,
Balance: 137,700 won]

491
00:17:49,995 --> 00:17:53,385
[Off he goes with the address
and water in hand]

492
00:17:55,634 --> 00:17:57,760
He's back!

493
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:59,896
- Where is it?
- Where's the place?

494
00:17:59,896 --> 00:18:02,726
Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo City.

495
00:18:02,726 --> 00:18:04,288
There it is on the map.

496
00:18:04,288 --> 00:18:06,278
- This is the way?
- Yeah.

497
00:18:06,278 --> 00:18:09,247
[About a 50-minute drive ahead]

498
00:18:09,247 --> 00:18:10,493
Picked up some water.

499
00:18:10,493 --> 00:18:11,708
Nice one.

500
00:18:11,708 --> 00:18:13,089
Did it come up the second you searched?

501
00:18:13,089 --> 00:18:14,168
Came right up.

502
00:18:14,168 --> 00:18:17,155
- What did you type in?
- "BTS V black pork."

503
00:18:17,155 --> 00:18:19,259
[Hahaha]

504
00:18:19,259 --> 00:18:21,088
Off we go.

505
00:18:21,088 --> 00:18:23,128
An hour, that's nothing.

506
00:18:23,128 --> 00:18:25,239
[6:38 PM, heading to the restaurant]

507
00:18:25,239 --> 00:18:26,729
How'd you get her to lend it?

508
00:18:26,729 --> 00:18:28,259
I just said... sorry to bother you...

509
00:18:28,259 --> 00:18:30,854
could you please look something up for me?

510
00:18:30,854 --> 00:18:33,538
- You asked her to search it?
- Yeah.

511
00:18:33,538 --> 00:18:35,473
You didn't catch the closing time, right?

512
00:18:35,473 --> 00:18:36,755
No, my head was spinning.

513
00:18:36,755 --> 00:18:39,074
Wish we could at least call ahead.

514
00:18:39,074 --> 00:18:41,112
- Call where?
- The restaurant.

515
00:18:41,112 --> 00:18:42,653
[Won't know
if it's open till they get there...]

516
00:18:42,653 --> 00:18:44,860
Ever done Jeju as a day trip?

517
00:18:44,860 --> 00:18:46,015
Never once.

518
00:18:46,015 --> 00:18:47,135
I have.

519
00:18:47,135 --> 00:18:48,687
- For work?
- Yeah.

520
00:18:48,687 --> 00:18:51,590
Pretty sure I've done it for work too.

521
00:18:51,590 --> 00:18:54,195
But never as an actual vacation.

522
00:18:54,195 --> 00:18:56,075
- This is amazing.
- Says it looks good?

523
00:18:56,075 --> 00:18:57,871
I'm saying it feels great right now.

524
00:18:57,871 --> 00:18:58,992
We're literally in Jeju.

525
00:18:58,992 --> 00:19:01,272
Right, just spotted a Baengnokdam sign.

526
00:19:01,272 --> 00:19:02,393
The lettering.

527
00:19:02,393 --> 00:19:04,271
[Even just the letters bring joy]
Yeah.

528
00:19:04,271 --> 00:19:06,631
Whoa, the ocean's killing it.

529
00:19:06,631 --> 00:19:09,374
Can't see a thing.

530
00:19:09,374 --> 00:19:10,415
[Even in pitch black, they're happy]

531
00:19:10,415 --> 00:19:11,643
Pitch black out there.

532
00:19:11,643 --> 00:19:12,872
Pure darkness.

533
00:19:12,872 --> 00:19:14,272
This is Jeju, right?

534
00:19:14,272 --> 00:19:16,159
Are we sure this isn't Boseong?

535
00:19:16,159 --> 00:19:19,172
Aren't we here to party in Jeju?

536
00:19:19,172 --> 00:19:20,472
- We should party on the last night.
- Right.

537
00:19:20,472 --> 00:19:22,032
Honestly, that works too.

538
00:19:22,032 --> 00:19:24,352
Right, let's just party straight
through till morning.

539
00:19:24,352 --> 00:19:26,069
- We can sleep on the plane.
- Yeah.

540
00:19:26,069 --> 00:19:28,830
- Swap with me if you get tired, okay?
- I'm not tired at all.

541
00:19:28,830 --> 00:19:30,762
I'm in full party mode right now.

542
00:19:30,762 --> 00:19:31,754
[Hehehe]

543
00:19:31,754 --> 00:19:34,065
But on camera, it looks like

544
00:19:34,065 --> 00:19:36,210
it's almost four in the morning.

545
00:19:36,210 --> 00:19:37,749
- Huh?
- More like 3 AM.

546
00:19:37,749 --> 00:19:38,969
It's really that dark?

547
00:19:38,969 --> 00:19:41,489
[Hard to believe, but it's actually 7 PM...]
Yeah, I bet nobody's visible.

548
00:19:41,489 --> 00:19:43,308
How much did we say we had left? 130,000 won?

549
00:19:43,308 --> 00:19:45,076
[137,700 won]
Yeah.

550
00:19:45,076 --> 00:19:46,626
Dinner, then heading to the accommodation?

551
00:19:46,626 --> 00:19:48,146
Once we get there...

552
00:19:48,146 --> 00:19:50,482
let's haggle before we order anything.

553
00:19:50,482 --> 00:19:52,651
[Looks like he's plotting something...]
Bet.

554
00:19:52,651 --> 00:19:54,099
[Revealed shortly]

555
00:19:54,099 --> 00:19:56,126
This is going to be so good.

556
00:19:56,126 --> 00:19:58,959
I mean, just so good.

557
00:19:58,959 --> 00:20:00,140
Can't wait.

558
00:20:00,140 --> 00:20:01,694
- Don't get your hopes too high.
- Don't expect too much.

559
00:20:01,694 --> 00:20:03,860
[Their highly anticipated first Jeju meal...]
No, just...

560
00:20:03,860 --> 00:20:05,697
The crew behind us must be hyped too.

561
00:20:05,697 --> 00:20:06,779
For real.

562
00:20:06,779 --> 00:20:08,667
If it's closed, total letdown.

563
00:20:08,667 --> 00:20:10,543
- Did you find the address on a blog?
- Yeah.

564
00:20:10,543 --> 00:20:12,077
- Or did you look it up on Naver?
- Yeah, on a blog.

565
00:20:12,077 --> 00:20:13,338
[Confirmed via blog review]

566
00:20:13,338 --> 00:20:15,239
When was that blog post from?

567
00:20:15,239 --> 00:20:17,842
- No clue.
- Something from 2021, maybe.

568
00:20:17,842 --> 00:20:20,078
[Like the mystery of the post date]

569
00:20:20,078 --> 00:20:24,641
[Heading down increasingly dark roads...]

570
00:20:24,641 --> 00:20:27,719
We're heading the right way, right?

571
00:20:27,719 --> 00:20:29,273
We are.

572
00:20:29,273 --> 00:20:30,927
Only 4.2 kilometers to go.

573
00:20:30,927 --> 00:20:32,290
Almost there.

574
00:20:32,290 --> 00:20:33,893
[Almost there, but the streets stay dark...]

575
00:20:33,893 --> 00:20:35,826
Please.

576
00:20:36,573 --> 00:20:39,634
Is it usually this dead around here?

577
00:20:39,634 --> 00:20:42,034
- Nothing in sight.
- Can't even see the road.

578
00:20:42,034 --> 00:20:45,704
On the way there, every light was off,

579
00:20:45,704 --> 00:20:47,739
pitch dark out, and so honestly,

580
00:20:47,739 --> 00:20:50,375
about five minutes before we got there,

581
00:20:50,375 --> 00:20:54,112
Seo Jun was getting a little tense.

582
00:20:54,112 --> 00:20:57,279
[Q. Any worries, since you picked it yourself?]

583
00:20:57,279 --> 00:20:59,559
I was terrified the place might be closed.

584
00:20:59,559 --> 00:21:01,640
And weekends in Jeju,
you never know if they're open.

585
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:04,119
Especially in a place like Jeju.

586
00:21:04,119 --> 00:21:07,192
Thinking about it,
if I picked it and it's shut,

587
00:21:07,192 --> 00:21:09,500
that puts me in a pretty awkward spot.

588
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:12,026
What if they relocated?

589
00:21:12,026 --> 00:21:13,899
[Bite your tongue...]
Maybe they moved to town.

590
00:21:13,899 --> 00:21:15,160
We're really here.

591
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:17,059
- Honestly so close now.
- Yeah.

592
00:21:17,059 --> 00:21:18,580
Finally made it.

593
00:21:18,580 --> 00:21:21,197
Cross your fingers and hope for the best.

594
00:21:21,197 --> 00:21:23,626
Smell of the sea.

595
00:21:23,626 --> 00:21:25,060
I can't see a thing.

596
00:21:25,060 --> 00:21:26,489
Seriously almost there.

597
00:21:26,489 --> 00:21:29,293
The further down we go, the darker it gets.

598
00:21:29,293 --> 00:21:32,426
Could there really be a pork place out here?

599
00:21:32,426 --> 00:21:34,169
Please!

600
00:21:34,169 --> 00:21:36,126
- Please!
- We're here.

601
00:21:36,126 --> 00:21:38,361
[Will the doors actually be open?]
Please!

602
00:21:38,361 --> 00:21:40,358
- It's open.
- It's open?

603
00:21:40,358 --> 00:21:42,092
- Is that really the place?
- Doors open?

604
00:21:42,092 --> 00:21:43,726
[The tension melts off the trio]
Doors are open.

605
00:21:43,726 --> 00:21:45,730
- Shall we head in?
- Good work.

606
00:21:45,730 --> 00:21:48,393
- Nice job.
- Nice job.

607
00:21:48,393 --> 00:21:50,203
[7:30 PM, black pork restaurant]

608
00:21:50,203 --> 00:21:52,203
[After an hour-long drive, they finally arrive]
Pretty wild, right?

609
00:21:53,306 --> 00:21:54,939
Sound of the waves! Waves crashing!

610
00:21:54,939 --> 00:21:56,393
My shoulders...

611
00:21:56,393 --> 00:21:57,693
With the waves as our side dish...

612
00:21:57,693 --> 00:21:58,693
- Sound of waves.
- This is insane.

613
00:21:58,693 --> 00:21:59,593
Yes.

614
00:21:59,593 --> 00:22:00,846
Shall we head inside now?

615
00:22:00,846 --> 00:22:02,380
Time to head in?

616
00:22:03,214 --> 00:22:05,150
[They walk in, hearts racing!]

617
00:22:05,150 --> 00:22:06,265
Hello there.

618
00:22:06,265 --> 00:22:07,685
Hello.

619
00:22:07,685 --> 00:22:09,226
- Hello.
- Oh my.

620
00:22:09,226 --> 00:22:10,454
Hello.

621
00:22:10,454 --> 00:22:12,048
[The owner rushes right over]
So nice to see you.

622
00:22:12,048 --> 00:22:13,288
It really has been a while.

623
00:22:13,288 --> 00:22:14,492
Hello.

624
00:22:14,492 --> 00:22:15,488
You know what?

625
00:22:15,488 --> 00:22:18,228
Folks from Japan come here all the time.

626
00:22:18,228 --> 00:22:19,876
- For real?
- I have no idea

627
00:22:19,876 --> 00:22:21,288
[She shares updates since their last visit]
how they manage to find our place.

628
00:22:21,288 --> 00:22:23,348
- Right.
- It blows my mind.

629
00:22:23,348 --> 00:22:26,171
- The four of you sitting over there.
- Yeah, right over there.

630
00:22:26,171 --> 00:22:28,293
- Right.
- They saw that and came looking.

631
00:22:28,293 --> 00:22:30,508
Would it be okay if we filmed ourselves eating?

632
00:22:30,508 --> 00:22:31,978
- Sure, go ahead.
- Thanks.

633
00:22:31,978 --> 00:22:33,945
- Please do.
- Yes.

634
00:22:33,945 --> 00:22:35,560
Want to eat over there then?

635
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:37,108
No other guests right now, right?

636
00:22:37,108 --> 00:22:38,626
- Nope, all empty.
- Then this spot, right here.

637
00:22:38,626 --> 00:22:40,385
[They settle in to sit down!]
- Yeah, filming's fine. - Thanks.

638
00:22:40,385 --> 00:22:42,453
- Thank you.
- Sure.

639
00:22:43,126 --> 00:22:45,724
- Here we are.
- Man, we actually made it.

640
00:22:45,724 --> 00:22:46,925
Truly made it.

641
00:22:46,925 --> 00:22:48,259
[An emotional sit-down!]

642
00:22:48,259 --> 00:22:51,038
I always loved having the ocean
right out front.

643
00:22:51,038 --> 00:22:53,384
Where's the ocean at?

644
00:22:53,384 --> 00:22:55,225
Was it this side? Or over that way?

645
00:22:55,225 --> 00:22:58,169
- Maybe over that side.
- It must be around here somewhere.

646
00:22:59,604 --> 00:23:03,974
[Hidden by the early darkness,
this place's true charm...]

647
00:23:05,410 --> 00:23:10,849
[Only reveals itself under sunlight]

648
00:23:10,849 --> 00:23:14,352
[Follow the sound of the waves, and...]

649
00:23:14,352 --> 00:23:19,691
[A spot appears right alongside the sea]

650
00:23:19,691 --> 00:23:23,027
[An ocean cradling Seongsan Ilchulbong]

651
00:23:23,027 --> 00:23:26,806
[Waves of yellow canola flowers
sway right out front]

652
00:23:28,099 --> 00:23:33,504
[Though they missed
the ocean view at sunset...]

653
00:23:33,504 --> 00:23:37,441
[Memories will fill in for the missing view]

654
00:23:38,182 --> 00:23:40,211
[Wistful]
This place is full of memories.

655
00:23:40,211 --> 00:23:42,893
[Adding one more memory tonight]

656
00:23:42,893 --> 00:23:44,052
Oh?

657
00:23:44,052 --> 00:23:46,462
- Prices aren't bad though.
- Right.

658
00:23:46,462 --> 00:23:49,520
[Daily price may vary]
10,900 won per 100 grams.

659
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:52,724
- One serving is around 200 grams.
- Yeah.

660
00:23:52,724 --> 00:23:54,102
- Not bad at all.
- Yeah.

661
00:23:54,102 --> 00:23:57,394
Meat would run us about 70,000 won then.

662
00:23:57,394 --> 00:24:00,231
- If we go with 600 grams.
- Right.

663
00:24:00,231 --> 00:24:01,409
What should we order?

664
00:24:01,409 --> 00:24:02,649
- Pork belly?
- Pork belly?

665
00:24:02,649 --> 00:24:05,248
- Pork belly first?
- Pork belly to start.

666
00:24:05,248 --> 00:24:07,238
[First order]
- 300 grams of pork belly? - Yeah.

667
00:24:07,238 --> 00:24:09,488
[Total 38,800 won]
300 grams of pork belly, please.

668
00:24:09,488 --> 00:24:10,742
- Sure.
- Thank you.

669
00:24:10,742 --> 00:24:12,210
[And the black pork express
takes off with pork belly!]

670
00:24:12,210 --> 00:24:14,726
How much do we have left?

671
00:24:14,726 --> 00:24:16,989
- Oh, right.
- It's over there.

672
00:24:16,989 --> 00:24:18,249
[Oops, wallet's in the car...]
We've got about...

673
00:24:18,249 --> 00:24:21,208
- 130,000...
- 138,000 won.

674
00:24:21,208 --> 00:24:24,122
I dropped 1,200 won on water.

675
00:24:24,122 --> 00:24:28,604
[Exact balance is 137,700 won]
137,000 won.

676
00:24:28,604 --> 00:24:30,465
But with 137,000 won,

677
00:24:30,465 --> 00:24:31,905
meat being 70,000 won,

678
00:24:31,905 --> 00:24:33,665
then...

679
00:24:33,665 --> 00:24:36,560
Hold on... lodging...

680
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:39,630
[No room booked yet
and they're about to blow over half...]

681
00:24:39,630 --> 00:24:41,784
Think we need to have a chat.

682
00:24:41,784 --> 00:24:44,042
Excuse me, would it be possible...

683
00:24:44,042 --> 00:24:46,010
to throw out

684
00:24:46,010 --> 00:24:48,513
- a little proposal?
- Nope.

685
00:24:48,513 --> 00:24:50,744
[That's harsh, isn't it?]

686
00:24:50,744 --> 00:24:53,202
Who even is that?

687
00:24:53,202 --> 00:24:55,604
Let's hear it then.

688
00:24:55,604 --> 00:24:57,815
See, the thing is,

689
00:24:57,815 --> 00:25:00,235
we went through hell to get here.

690
00:25:00,235 --> 00:25:03,332
And turns out,

691
00:25:03,332 --> 00:25:06,965
the ferry costs more than we figured.

692
00:25:06,965 --> 00:25:09,767
[Negotiation tactic 1: Logical persuasion]

693
00:25:09,767 --> 00:25:11,893
And tomorrow too,

694
00:25:11,893 --> 00:25:14,539
we'd technically be getting a benefit.

695
00:25:14,539 --> 00:25:16,674
So here's the thing,

696
00:25:16,674 --> 00:25:19,210
what we're proposing is,

697
00:25:19,210 --> 00:25:21,660
since we won't be claiming tomorrow's benefit,

698
00:25:21,660 --> 00:25:23,827
that benefit could be...

699
00:25:23,827 --> 00:25:25,068
basically,

700
00:25:25,068 --> 00:25:28,126
we wanted to talk it over with you.

701
00:25:28,126 --> 00:25:30,092
[Quick backpedal...]
Yeah.

702
00:25:30,092 --> 00:25:32,390
You want to pull tomorrow's benefit forward.

703
00:25:32,390 --> 00:25:36,226
- Right.
- Put simply, can we cash in early?

704
00:25:36,226 --> 00:25:39,597
You'd just pull a phone again anyway.

705
00:25:39,597 --> 00:25:40,831
[Yikes... that's hitting a sore spot...]

706
00:25:40,831 --> 00:25:42,972
That's selling us short.

707
00:25:42,972 --> 00:25:46,792
We've each pulled a phone already.

708
00:25:46,792 --> 00:25:47,972
Even if we pulled phones,

709
00:25:47,972 --> 00:25:50,308
selling them on Karrot for a million won each,

710
00:25:50,308 --> 00:25:51,793
- True.
- that'd be sweet.

711
00:25:51,793 --> 00:25:52,927
[A creative-economy angle]

712
00:25:52,927 --> 00:25:54,473
Honestly, I don't even need the phone.

713
00:25:54,473 --> 00:25:57,560
Don't need it.

714
00:25:57,560 --> 00:25:59,717
[Negotiation tactic 2: Push and pull]
So could we somehow...

715
00:25:59,717 --> 00:26:02,352
- And it is the last night.
- Sure.

716
00:26:02,352 --> 00:26:04,259
The real reason we came to Jeju

717
00:26:04,259 --> 00:26:06,591
was to throw a party.

718
00:26:06,591 --> 00:26:08,233
[Reading the room...]

719
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:10,259
Jeju party.

720
00:26:10,259 --> 00:26:13,364
- What's the show called? Unplanned Trip.
- Right.

721
00:26:13,364 --> 00:26:14,437
[Negotiation tactic 3: Emotional appeal]

722
00:26:14,437 --> 00:26:16,193
Give us some youth here.

723
00:26:16,193 --> 00:26:18,259
[Scratch]
No, but still...

724
00:26:18,259 --> 00:26:19,460
Scratch...

725
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:20,393
Scratch...

726
00:26:20,393 --> 00:26:21,893
[Looks like this is the end...]
About the lodging...

727
00:26:21,893 --> 00:26:24,842
Okay, so if you pull the benefit forward,

728
00:26:24,842 --> 00:26:25,726
- Yes.
- Yes.

729
00:26:25,726 --> 00:26:28,913
the lodging we've covered so far

730
00:26:28,913 --> 00:26:32,000
averages around 150,000 won?

731
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:33,133
- Well...
- Yesterday...

732
00:26:33,133 --> 00:26:34,460
Then let's do this...

733
00:26:34,460 --> 00:26:36,179
One moment.

734
00:26:36,179 --> 00:26:38,356
We need a quick huddle.

735
00:26:38,356 --> 00:26:39,423
[Emergency three-way huddle begins]

736
00:26:39,423 --> 00:26:41,560
So what if...

737
00:26:41,560 --> 00:26:43,387
the benefit options

738
00:26:43,387 --> 00:26:45,463
swap car, phone, lodging out

739
00:26:45,463 --> 00:26:48,340
for 50,000 won, 100,000 won, 150,000 won?

740
00:26:48,340 --> 00:26:49,788
- Not bad.
- And we draw from those!

741
00:26:49,788 --> 00:26:51,835
- That's a solid idea.
- Yeah, not bad.

742
00:26:52,460 --> 00:26:54,188
We've got a good idea cooking.

743
00:26:54,188 --> 00:26:55,228
Lay it on us.

744
00:26:55,228 --> 00:26:58,959
If we go too crazy with this,

745
00:26:58,959 --> 00:27:01,712
- it kind of breaks the show's vibe.
- Right.

746
00:27:01,712 --> 00:27:04,059
Honestly though,

747
00:27:04,059 --> 00:27:06,227
- more is always better.
- Of course.

748
00:27:06,227 --> 00:27:09,237
- But we do have a conscience.
- We have one.

749
00:27:09,237 --> 00:27:12,191
So we always had those three benefits.

750
00:27:12,191 --> 00:27:15,657
- Originally phone, car, lodging.
- Right.

751
00:27:15,657 --> 00:27:18,429
So swap out phone, lodging, car,

752
00:27:18,429 --> 00:27:21,732
- Yeah, swap them.
- plug in 50,000, 100,000, 150,000 won,

753
00:27:21,732 --> 00:27:23,437
and we draw from those.

754
00:27:23,437 --> 00:27:27,405
Lodging was usually around 150,000 won.

755
00:27:27,405 --> 00:27:30,774
So you want to swap lodging out
for 150,000 won cash.

756
00:27:30,774 --> 00:27:32,401
- Exactly.
- The car becomes

757
00:27:32,401 --> 00:27:34,212
- 100,000 won as a rental fee.
- Right.

758
00:27:34,212 --> 00:27:35,893
- Right.
- About 100,000 won covers it.

759
00:27:35,893 --> 00:27:38,983
Phone day-use fee, around 50,000 won.

760
00:27:38,983 --> 00:27:40,885
[Lodging fee, 150,000 won,
Car rental, 100,000 won]

761
00:27:40,885 --> 00:27:42,359
[Phone rental, 50,000 won]

762
00:27:42,359 --> 00:27:44,159
5, 10, 15... let us huddle for a sec.

763
00:27:44,159 --> 00:27:45,232
Sure.

764
00:27:45,232 --> 00:27:46,692
Take your time.

765
00:27:46,692 --> 00:27:48,494
Please help us out.

766
00:27:48,494 --> 00:27:51,811
We'll let them use that cash
to cover all of tomorrow.

767
00:27:51,811 --> 00:27:53,898
- The flight's already covered by allowance.
- That's done.

768
00:27:53,898 --> 00:27:56,059
- Subway.
- Even the ride from Gimpo to the office

769
00:27:56,059 --> 00:27:57,702
- has to come out of that money.
- Okay.

770
00:27:57,702 --> 00:28:00,326
[A heated second huddle on this side...]
So, once we hit Jeju City...

771
00:28:00,326 --> 00:28:03,459
The biggest problem is leaving Gimpo,

772
00:28:03,459 --> 00:28:04,626
heading to the live shoot,

773
00:28:04,626 --> 00:28:05,893
- Right.
- we'll need a cab.

774
00:28:05,893 --> 00:28:07,927
- The deal is ready.
- Which means we need to draw 15.

775
00:28:07,927 --> 00:28:09,193
Okay.

776
00:28:09,193 --> 00:28:11,115
The deal is ready.

777
00:28:11,115 --> 00:28:13,584
Tomorrow's allowance

778
00:28:13,584 --> 00:28:15,920
- went to the flight, that's settled.
- Yes.

779
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:18,522
- No allowance owed to you.
- Correct.

780
00:28:18,522 --> 00:28:22,160
Whether you draw 5, 10, or 15,

781
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:23,895
all the way until you reach
the office tomorrow,

782
00:28:23,895 --> 00:28:26,642
Seoul transport is included in that cash.

783
00:28:26,642 --> 00:28:28,061
- Right.
- Right.

784
00:28:28,061 --> 00:28:30,102
- Subway, walking, whatever.
- Hitchhike if we have to.

785
00:28:30,102 --> 00:28:31,281
Of course.

786
00:28:31,281 --> 00:28:32,992
We're ready.

787
00:28:32,992 --> 00:28:34,807
Yes, for now.

788
00:28:34,807 --> 00:28:37,293
Okay, let's do this.

789
00:28:37,293 --> 00:28:39,131
[Deal sealed]
Deal.

790
00:28:39,131 --> 00:28:41,871
So who's drawing this time?

791
00:28:41,871 --> 00:28:43,581
- Woo Shik, you draw.
- Yumi, you should draw.

792
00:28:43,581 --> 00:28:44,552
- No way.
- I already drew the car earlier.

793
00:28:44,552 --> 00:28:45,985
[The final fate weighs heavily...]
I drew the phone and the car.

794
00:28:45,985 --> 00:28:48,660
Just draw the 15, easy.

795
00:28:48,660 --> 00:28:51,760
- Don't overthink it.
- You seem lucky today.

796
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:53,531
- You pulled the car too.
- Doubt it.

797
00:28:53,531 --> 00:28:55,652
Listen, our storyline today is hot.

798
00:28:55,652 --> 00:28:57,432
[Lucky narrative 1]
Because we spotted a clunker.

799
00:28:57,432 --> 00:28:58,996
- You spotted the clunker.
- And then,

800
00:28:58,996 --> 00:29:01,352
[Lucky narrative 2]
hit up Tto* Bakery with zero line.

801
00:29:01,352 --> 00:29:03,359
- True.
- Right?

802
00:29:03,359 --> 00:29:05,052
[Lucky narrative 3]
Nailed the time and scored coffee.

803
00:29:05,052 --> 00:29:06,687
- Right?
- Yeah.

804
00:29:06,687 --> 00:29:08,460
That time-guessing thing.

805
00:29:08,460 --> 00:29:10,388
You called 35 minutes right on the dot.

806
00:29:10,388 --> 00:29:11,927
- We did it together.
- Not just anyone can pull that off.

807
00:29:11,927 --> 00:29:13,087
Yeah.

808
00:29:13,087 --> 00:29:15,179
Then let's all three of us draw together.

809
00:29:15,179 --> 00:29:17,181
[Wait... that's actually a good idea...]
Let's draw it together.

810
00:29:17,181 --> 00:29:18,851
How do we draw together?

811
00:29:18,851 --> 00:29:20,793
- Stick our hands in first.
- Yeah.

812
00:29:20,793 --> 00:29:22,620
- With our hands...
- Inside the container,

813
00:29:22,620 --> 00:29:24,687
- feel this one, feel that one?
- Yeah.

814
00:29:24,687 --> 00:29:26,028
Where are we drawing from?

815
00:29:26,028 --> 00:29:27,068
What container then?

816
00:29:27,068 --> 00:29:29,760
- Tissue box.
- The tissue box.

817
00:29:29,760 --> 00:29:31,987
- Let us see it.
- I'll show you.

818
00:29:31,987 --> 00:29:33,531
- Wrote it out, exactly 50,000 won.
- Yes.

819
00:29:33,531 --> 00:29:34,765
[Never a dull moment, right to the end...]

820
00:29:34,765 --> 00:29:37,393
[Folds each slip neatly, twice,
right in front of them...]

821
00:29:37,393 --> 00:29:38,704
All three together.

822
00:29:38,704 --> 00:29:40,207
[Drops them straight into the draw box]
Just toss them in here?

823
00:29:40,207 --> 00:29:42,105
Going in.

824
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:46,023
I can guarantee a 100,000 won pull.

825
00:29:46,023 --> 00:29:48,426
[Where's that confidence from?]
So aiming for 100,000 won? Because...

826
00:29:48,426 --> 00:29:50,293
- 100% I'll pull it.
- Trusting you.

827
00:29:50,293 --> 00:29:51,282
Then you draw.

828
00:29:51,282 --> 00:29:52,667
- So going for 10?
- Yeah.

829
00:29:52,667 --> 00:29:54,453
But we don't need the 15?

830
00:29:54,453 --> 00:29:56,287
- Why 10?
- Going with 10.

831
00:29:56,287 --> 00:29:58,222
- Sticking with 10?
- Yeah.

832
00:29:58,222 --> 00:29:59,188
[The lucky guy revving up
with self-hypnosis...]

833
00:29:59,188 --> 00:30:00,703
Then shall we do it? You wanna do it?

834
00:30:00,703 --> 00:30:03,557
- But we could draw 5, or we could draw 15.
- That's true.

835
00:30:03,557 --> 00:30:05,663
- It's okay.
- But 100,000 won is 100%.

836
00:30:05,663 --> 00:30:08,627
[At this point, it's almost scary...]
- Oh, really? - Okay.

837
00:30:08,627 --> 00:30:10,366
I'm starting to trust you.

838
00:30:10,366 --> 00:30:11,548
Is 100,000 won enough for us?

839
00:30:11,548 --> 00:30:13,447
- Yeah, yeah.
- Yeah.

840
00:30:13,447 --> 00:30:14,778
Woo Shik, want to do it?

841
00:30:14,778 --> 00:30:15,964
- Yeah.
- Okay.

842
00:30:15,964 --> 00:30:18,261
[The star of the final benefit draw]
I'll open the lid for you.

843
00:30:18,261 --> 00:30:19,416
Oh, the lid, uh...

844
00:30:19,416 --> 00:30:22,380
[Will he really draw 100,000 won
as confidently predicted?]

845
00:30:22,380 --> 00:30:24,726
- Oh, without looking?
- Yes, don't look.

846
00:30:24,726 --> 00:30:28,620
[Under tight surveillance,
he sharpens his senses...]

847
00:30:28,620 --> 00:30:29,645
[Fidgeting]

848
00:30:29,645 --> 00:30:32,321
Maybe his hand has eyes.

849
00:30:32,321 --> 00:30:35,385
[His eyes are actually up here]

850
00:30:35,385 --> 00:30:37,502
[Laughing]

851
00:30:37,502 --> 00:30:39,004
What? Aren't they all the same paper?

852
00:30:39,004 --> 00:30:40,468
- What should I do? Should I pick one?
- You're picking now?

853
00:30:40,468 --> 00:30:44,276
- This is definitely a 10. One hundred percent.
- One hundred percent? Okay, let's go then.

854
00:30:44,276 --> 00:30:46,066
- Should I go with this one?
- Go for it.

855
00:30:46,066 --> 00:30:47,846
[The final benefit... has been drawn!]
Alright, it's drawn.

856
00:30:47,846 --> 00:30:49,199
Come on, gather around!

857
00:30:49,199 --> 00:30:50,724
Gather up like before.

858
00:30:50,724 --> 00:30:52,525
[Getting addicted to the suspense]
- Let's see. - But...

859
00:30:52,525 --> 00:30:55,058
[How much is written on the slip?]
- Ever since earlier... - Let's see.

860
00:30:55,058 --> 00:30:56,700
[Going right in!]
Let's see what it is.

861
00:30:56,700 --> 00:30:59,312
- Wait.
- You have to accept whatever comes up.

862
00:30:59,312 --> 00:31:02,011
- Open it up.
- A little more.

863
00:31:03,811 --> 00:31:06,622
[A faint line comes into view...]
Hey, it's a 1. It's a 1!

864
00:31:06,622 --> 00:31:09,660
Hey, it's a 1. It's a 1!

865
00:31:09,660 --> 00:31:11,153
[What do we do?]

866
00:31:11,153 --> 00:31:12,675
Hey, it's a 1. It's a 1!

867
00:31:12,675 --> 00:31:14,361
- It's not 10,000 won, right?
- Yeah.

868
00:31:14,361 --> 00:31:16,713
- Did you write the word "won" too?
- We wrote "won" too.

869
00:31:16,713 --> 00:31:19,479
[It could just be the first syllable of "won"]
This... is it?

870
00:31:19,479 --> 00:31:20,566
- Go? Just go for it?
- Go.

871
00:31:20,566 --> 00:31:23,226
- Just open it all the way?
- No, just a little more. Halfway.

872
00:31:23,226 --> 00:31:25,079
Just a little more.

873
00:31:25,079 --> 00:31:27,306
- It's a 1, it's a 1!
- It's a 1!

874
00:31:27,306 --> 00:31:29,158
[Excitement MAX]
It's a 1, it's a 1!

875
00:31:29,158 --> 00:31:31,041
How did you write the 5?

876
00:31:31,041 --> 00:31:32,722
- This is it.
- We wrote it as a numeral.

877
00:31:32,722 --> 00:31:35,362
- Wait. Ah, I think it's 10.
- No, it's not...

878
00:31:35,362 --> 00:31:37,349
[Frugal or luxury, what's it gonna be?]
- It's 10. - Let's take a look.

879
00:31:38,382 --> 00:31:40,010
- Ah, 10!
- Oh!

880
00:31:40,010 --> 00:31:41,617
[Won 100,000 won]
It's 10!

881
00:31:41,617 --> 00:31:43,177
Isn't this crazy?

882
00:31:43,177 --> 00:31:46,342
[Everything the lucky guy says comes true]
- What? - Wow, you really drew the 10?

883
00:31:46,342 --> 00:31:47,788
- How did you get that?
- How did you get that?

884
00:31:47,788 --> 00:31:49,385
Wow, how did you get that?

885
00:31:49,385 --> 00:31:52,274
- If it's 10, that should cover your expenses.
- That 100,000 won from earlier...

886
00:31:52,274 --> 00:31:54,212
[230,000 won for meat, lodging, and tomorrow]
- 10 is great. - 10 is enough.

887
00:31:54,212 --> 00:31:55,404
If it's 10, that's enough.

888
00:31:55,404 --> 00:31:57,404
- Nice!
- Wow.

889
00:31:57,404 --> 00:31:59,509
So what now? Meat party tonight?

890
00:31:59,509 --> 00:32:02,127
- It's a party tonight!
- Party tonight!

891
00:32:02,127 --> 00:32:04,413
I was certain it'd be 100,000 won.

892
00:32:04,413 --> 00:32:06,834
- You said 100% you'd draw 100,000 won.
- Yeah.

893
00:32:06,834 --> 00:32:09,649
[I knew you'd do it]
- But you sounded so confident. - Right?

894
00:32:09,649 --> 00:32:11,500
Thanks for trusting me.

895
00:32:11,500 --> 00:32:13,050
I just went with confidence.

896
00:32:13,050 --> 00:32:15,241
I knew I could draw 100,000 won.

897
00:32:15,241 --> 00:32:17,359
And if I had drawn 50,000 won,

898
00:32:17,359 --> 00:32:19,551
we'd cut back on the lodging that day

899
00:32:19,551 --> 00:32:22,174
and definitely use that
50,000 won for taxi fares.

900
00:32:22,174 --> 00:32:24,233
That was actually the angle I was going for.

901
00:32:24,233 --> 00:32:27,650
So we could travel a bit more comfortably...

902
00:32:27,650 --> 00:32:29,924
Where does that confidence come from?

903
00:32:29,924 --> 00:32:34,635
But he also won the car,
so his luck must be real.

904
00:32:34,635 --> 00:32:39,489
I think all the luck was
with Woo Shik that day.

905
00:32:39,489 --> 00:32:40,736
He really got 100,000 won.

906
00:32:40,736 --> 00:32:42,326
[The moment the universe's energy
aligned with Woo Shik...]

907
00:32:42,326 --> 00:32:44,993
We'll give you the 100,000 won right away.

908
00:32:44,993 --> 00:32:46,058
[Balance: 237,700 won]

909
00:32:46,058 --> 00:32:47,386
Put it in your pocket first.

910
00:32:47,386 --> 00:32:49,311
Wow, we're lucky today.

911
00:32:49,311 --> 00:32:51,699
[And right on cue, the pork belly arrives]

912
00:32:51,699 --> 00:32:53,073
[Straight onto the grill!]

913
00:32:53,073 --> 00:32:55,373
- Alright, let's go.
- Let's go.

914
00:32:56,312 --> 00:32:59,285
Should we get 300g
of pork shoulder too? Right now?

915
00:32:59,285 --> 00:33:00,433
Yeah, let's do that.

916
00:33:00,433 --> 00:33:02,690
[Quick response to keep the momentum going]

917
00:33:02,690 --> 00:33:04,900
Excuse me, could we get
300g of pork shoulder as well?

918
00:33:04,900 --> 00:33:05,966
Yes.

919
00:33:05,966 --> 00:33:07,864
[Pork Belly 300g 38,800 won, Pork Shoulder 300g
31,200 won, Total 70,000 won]

920
00:33:07,864 --> 00:33:09,174
That really is thick.

921
00:33:09,174 --> 00:33:10,630
[Nods]

922
00:33:10,630 --> 00:33:13,155
[A hearty thickness that locks in the juices]

923
00:33:13,155 --> 00:33:14,735
That looks kind of hard to cook.

924
00:33:14,735 --> 00:33:16,902
Nah, I'm good at grilling thick cuts.

925
00:33:16,902 --> 00:33:18,110
[Sits up properly...]

926
00:33:18,110 --> 00:33:20,493
[I'll show you from here]

927
00:33:20,493 --> 00:33:25,351
[Starts cutting the golden-brown
pork belly into bite-sized pieces]

928
00:33:25,351 --> 00:33:27,782
[Speeding things up and
cutting it into easy-to-eat pieces...]

929
00:33:27,782 --> 00:33:30,701
[Thought that was it?]

930
00:33:30,701 --> 00:33:34,087
[Lines up the sides too,
making sure they get equal attention]

931
00:33:34,087 --> 00:33:36,014
Torture us, torture us.

932
00:33:36,014 --> 00:33:37,909
[Roll]

933
00:33:39,604 --> 00:33:41,255
- Yumi, I think this one's ready to eat.
- Yeah.

934
00:33:41,255 --> 00:33:43,443
- Yumi, you try it first.
- Right.

935
00:33:43,443 --> 00:33:46,217
[The younger brothers always
look after Yumi first]

936
00:33:46,217 --> 00:33:49,968
[Into the sauce, then the mouth]

937
00:33:50,566 --> 00:33:52,156
We took a ferry just to eat this.

938
00:33:52,156 --> 00:33:53,552
How is it?

939
00:33:53,552 --> 00:33:54,567
It's so good.

940
00:33:54,567 --> 00:33:57,006
[Getting emotional]
Oh, it's that good?

941
00:33:57,006 --> 00:33:59,584
[Woo Shik takes his first bite
with his winning combo: ssamjang]

942
00:34:02,860 --> 00:34:05,043
Let's try it with the salted anchovy sauce.

943
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:06,048
It's good.

944
00:34:06,048 --> 00:34:09,044
[Chef Park takes a bite with the classic
Jeju combo: salted anchovy sauce]

945
00:34:13,831 --> 00:34:15,582
This is it.

946
00:34:15,582 --> 00:34:17,816
- It's delicious.
- Yeah.

947
00:34:17,816 --> 00:34:19,650
[Up next after the pork belly...]

948
00:34:19,650 --> 00:34:21,635
I think the pork shoulder
is going to be so good.

949
00:34:21,635 --> 00:34:24,468
[Keeping the momentum going,
the pork shoulder makes its entrance]

950
00:34:24,468 --> 00:34:25,892
[Sneaking a peek at the crew]

951
00:34:25,892 --> 00:34:28,017
Ah, the skirt meat looks good too.

952
00:34:28,017 --> 00:34:29,285
We can spend 100,000 won here.

953
00:34:29,285 --> 00:34:30,753
- 100,000 won?
- Yeah.

954
00:34:30,753 --> 00:34:33,448
We'd still have 130,000 won left.

955
00:34:33,448 --> 00:34:35,569
Yeah, then should we order some skirt meat?

956
00:34:35,569 --> 00:34:37,261
- Do you know another way?
- What?

957
00:34:37,261 --> 00:34:38,769
Just eat two bowls of rice.

958
00:34:38,769 --> 00:34:40,363
[That's genius?]

959
00:34:40,363 --> 00:34:42,261
Then we'll have two bowls of rice.

960
00:34:42,261 --> 00:34:43,849
- One soybean paste stew?
- Yeah.

961
00:34:43,849 --> 00:34:46,418
[Total 77,000 won]
- One soybean paste stew, please. - Yes.

962
00:34:46,418 --> 00:34:48,083
What about the skirt meat?

963
00:34:48,083 --> 00:34:51,626
And two servings of skirt meat as well.

964
00:34:51,626 --> 00:34:52,987
[Meanwhile, the pork neck waits
after soaking up that smoky flavor]

965
00:34:52,987 --> 00:34:54,388
- I think it's ready to eat.
- I think it's ready.

966
00:34:54,388 --> 00:34:55,453
You can eat it.

967
00:34:55,453 --> 00:34:57,948
- Oh, can I eat this?
- You can eat it.

968
00:34:57,948 --> 00:35:01,060
[Then Yumi takes a big bite of pork shoulder]

969
00:35:03,925 --> 00:35:07,192
[Meanwhile, a huge bite of a perilla leaf wrap]

970
00:35:08,885 --> 00:35:10,935
[If you're wondering what it tastes like...]

971
00:35:10,935 --> 00:35:13,431
[It tastes like this]

972
00:35:13,431 --> 00:35:15,472
Then add some green onions...

973
00:35:15,472 --> 00:35:18,517
[Wrapped neatly in lettuce
and headed straight into the mouth]

974
00:35:19,264 --> 00:35:21,284
[Jeju seal]

975
00:35:21,284 --> 00:35:24,694
[The seal clap makes an appearance
in Jeju after Gwangju]

976
00:35:24,694 --> 00:35:27,429
Wait, then tomorrow we...

977
00:35:27,429 --> 00:35:29,902
wake up at 6 AM...

978
00:35:29,902 --> 00:35:32,248
- We need to leave at 6 AM.
- Oh, we have to leave at 6 AM.

979
00:35:32,248 --> 00:35:33,508
To be safe.

980
00:35:33,508 --> 00:35:34,892
[For reference: Their flight is
at 7:10 AM tomorrow]

981
00:35:34,892 --> 00:35:39,394
Wow, then we've got time until 6 AM tomorrow?
If we don't sleep.

982
00:35:39,394 --> 00:35:42,172
[No response from Po-po &amp; Almost-40 Seo Jun]
That's right. If you don't sleep.

983
00:35:42,172 --> 00:35:44,640
Wow, we can hang out for 10 hours.

984
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:47,133
I can already picture Woo Shik
looking like this...

985
00:35:47,133 --> 00:35:50,310
[Log out]
around midnight.

986
00:35:50,310 --> 00:35:53,202
[At this moment, Woo Shik's
brightest eyes are focused on...]

987
00:35:53,202 --> 00:35:55,819
[The long-awaited skirt meat]

988
00:35:55,819 --> 00:35:57,802
You're grilling it well.

989
00:35:57,802 --> 00:36:00,449
I've grilled a lot of meat.

990
00:36:00,449 --> 00:36:01,956
- The skirt meat?
- Yes.

991
00:36:01,956 --> 00:36:04,249
[Chef Park, who supervised it all,
takes the first bite...]

992
00:36:04,249 --> 00:36:07,003
Yum, the juices are bursting.

993
00:36:07,003 --> 00:36:10,411
[Blowing on it and savoring the final meat]

994
00:36:10,411 --> 00:36:12,610
It's delicious.

995
00:36:12,610 --> 00:36:15,414
[Woo Shik making it
just in time for skirt steak]

996
00:36:16,631 --> 00:36:19,085
[So good, he grabs his neck]

997
00:36:19,085 --> 00:36:21,952
Skirt steak's good too, huh?

998
00:36:21,952 --> 00:36:24,646
We should put rice in
this soybean paste stew and boil it...

999
00:36:24,646 --> 00:36:26,967
I only had a little of this.

1000
00:36:26,967 --> 00:36:29,633
- Should we try it?
- Yeah.

1001
00:36:29,633 --> 00:36:33,010
[Seo Jun's Soybean-Stew Rice]
[Step 1. Scrape all the rice into the stew]

1002
00:36:33,010 --> 00:36:37,082
[Step 2. Mix it so the broth soaks in]

1003
00:36:37,082 --> 00:36:39,823
But I don't think it'll work
because there's not much broth.

1004
00:36:39,823 --> 00:36:42,177
[Step 3. Put it on the grill,
and let it simmer gently]

1005
00:36:42,177 --> 00:36:45,716
[Let it reduce like this for five minutes...]

1006
00:36:48,432 --> 00:36:52,335
[The perfect finale
to cut through the richness]

1007
00:36:52,335 --> 00:36:54,167
What kind of rice dish is that?

1008
00:36:54,167 --> 00:36:55,561
Soybean stew rice.

1009
00:36:55,561 --> 00:36:57,794
Rice made with leftover soybean stew.

1010
00:36:57,794 --> 00:37:00,049
[Taking a big spoonful
of the leftover soybean-stew rice]

1011
00:37:00,049 --> 00:37:01,102
Soybean stew...

1012
00:37:01,102 --> 00:37:03,601
- It's hot.
- It's hot? I'll eat it in a bit.

1013
00:37:03,601 --> 00:37:07,252
[Yumi blows on it and takes a bite...]

1014
00:37:07,252 --> 00:37:09,143
[Carbs never lie]

1015
00:37:09,143 --> 00:37:11,608
[Even Woo Shik finishes
with the Korean dessert]

1016
00:37:13,590 --> 00:37:14,984
This is delicious.

1017
00:37:14,984 --> 00:37:16,669
Are you making it too?

1018
00:37:16,669 --> 00:37:18,310
[We're copying you right away]

1019
00:37:18,310 --> 00:37:19,950
Oh, everyone's making it.

1020
00:37:19,950 --> 00:37:21,223
You're right.

1021
00:37:21,223 --> 00:37:24,835
Doing this show really
makes everyone eat together.

1022
00:37:24,835 --> 00:37:27,128
[A community bound by fate,
even through the last meal...]

1023
00:37:27,128 --> 00:37:30,744
- Ah, I think this is fine.
- If you guys don't go, we won't get to eat.

1024
00:37:30,744 --> 00:37:34,078
And if you don't book a place to stay,
we can't book one either...

1025
00:37:34,078 --> 00:37:37,142
That's true. We don't have
a place to stay right now.

1026
00:37:37,142 --> 00:37:39,681
[Thrilling, where will they sleep tonight?]

1027
00:37:39,681 --> 00:37:44,101
Even a place to stay tonight
would make everything perfect.

1028
00:37:44,101 --> 00:37:45,961
Thanks for the meal. We should pay now.

1029
00:37:45,961 --> 00:37:48,422
- Excuse us, we'd like to pay.
- We need to bring money, right?

1030
00:37:48,422 --> 00:37:49,876
[Balance: 137,000 won]
700...

1031
00:37:49,876 --> 00:37:51,046
100,700 won?

1032
00:37:51,046 --> 00:37:53,442
- 700 won... yeah, 100,700 won.
- Wow, that's perfect.

1033
00:37:53,442 --> 00:37:55,582
[Payment completed with collected change!]
Here's 100,700 won.

1034
00:37:55,582 --> 00:37:57,229
- Thank you.
- Thank you for the meal.

1035
00:37:57,229 --> 00:37:59,192
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you for the meal.

1036
00:37:59,192 --> 00:38:00,781
- I'll come again next time.
- Thank you.

1037
00:38:00,781 --> 00:38:02,271
Thank you for the meal.

1038
00:38:02,271 --> 00:38:03,392
It's cold.

1039
00:38:03,392 --> 00:38:05,571
[The Jeju breeze greets them
the moment they step outside]

1040
00:38:05,571 --> 00:38:07,603
[So cold...]

1041
00:38:07,603 --> 00:38:11,164
[Quickly getting into the car
to escape the wind]

1042
00:38:11,164 --> 00:38:13,072
They actually raise their own pigs.

1043
00:38:13,072 --> 00:38:16,690
[Even regular customers didn't know this]
- Her husband does. - That explains it.

1044
00:38:16,690 --> 00:38:18,775
Oh, your legs are pretty long, huh?

1045
00:38:20,060 --> 00:38:22,125
[Big sis is the driver this time]
Well, I...

1046
00:38:22,125 --> 00:38:23,980
Take it slow.

1047
00:38:24,829 --> 00:38:26,569
Where should I set the navigation?

1048
00:38:26,569 --> 00:38:27,642
Somewhere around here?

1049
00:38:27,642 --> 00:38:29,370
[They need to find a place to sleep tonight...]

1050
00:38:29,370 --> 00:38:31,183
- Search all.
- Search all.

1051
00:38:31,183 --> 00:38:34,200
[Using the navigation search function
since they don't have phones]

1052
00:38:34,200 --> 00:38:36,824
Accommodation near Jeju Airport!

1053
00:38:38,349 --> 00:38:40,714
[Recognition error]

1054
00:38:40,714 --> 00:38:42,169
Should we just head to the airport?

1055
00:38:42,169 --> 00:38:44,424
- Jeju City?
- Just... Jeju City.

1056
00:38:44,424 --> 00:38:47,337
- Jeju City Hall?
- Jeju City Hall? Got it.

1057
00:38:48,038 --> 00:38:50,147
You're saying we should head downtown first.

1058
00:38:50,147 --> 00:38:54,908
[Planning to find accommodation
downtown near the airport]

1059
00:38:54,908 --> 00:38:56,275
We're really going now.

1060
00:38:56,275 --> 00:38:57,428
[9:35 PM, departing for downtown Jeju]

1061
00:38:57,428 --> 00:38:59,192
Oh, we'll arrive at 10:35 PM.

1062
00:38:59,192 --> 00:39:01,300
Wow, it takes an hour?

1063
00:39:01,300 --> 00:39:03,201
Yeah, it took an hour on the way here too.

1064
00:39:03,208 --> 00:39:05,326
[Late at night... will they be able to
walk in and get a room?]

1065
00:39:05,339 --> 00:39:08,617
Wow, being in Jeju only at night is really...

1066
00:39:08,617 --> 00:39:09,660
It's my first time.

1067
00:39:09,660 --> 00:39:12,711
It's really a new experience.

1068
00:39:12,711 --> 00:39:15,311
This beautiful scenery... huh?

1069
00:39:15,311 --> 00:39:17,663
- Scenery.
- The scenery...

1070
00:39:17,663 --> 00:39:20,057
We can't see any of it.

1071
00:39:20,057 --> 00:39:23,208
So this is Seopjikoji Cape.

1072
00:39:23,208 --> 00:39:26,346
[Only the sign is visible]

1073
00:39:26,346 --> 00:39:28,971
There's an ocean right in front of us.

1074
00:39:28,971 --> 00:39:31,625
[Pitch black]
- Where? - I can't see it.

1075
00:39:31,625 --> 00:39:33,604
The ocean's usually at one o'clock.

1076
00:39:33,604 --> 00:39:35,405
Don't lie.

1077
00:39:35,405 --> 00:39:39,627
[The coastal road view at 1 o'clock
that they'd have seen during the day...]

1078
00:39:39,636 --> 00:39:44,364
Oh, this is good. Really good.

1079
00:39:44,364 --> 00:39:46,639
But I really like this kind of...

1080
00:39:46,639 --> 00:39:50,265
I really... love trips like this.

1081
00:39:50,265 --> 00:39:51,747
Seriously.

1082
00:39:51,747 --> 00:39:53,629
Honestly, we're fun
even when we don't do anything.

1083
00:39:53,629 --> 00:39:54,657
True.

1084
00:39:54,657 --> 00:39:57,354
[Last-night vibes]

1085
00:39:57,354 --> 00:39:59,541
- But while traveling...
- Yeah.

1086
00:39:59,541 --> 00:40:04,250
We've never traveled with
so many restrictions before.

1087
00:40:04,250 --> 00:40:05,613
Right.

1088
00:40:06,236 --> 00:40:09,074
But putting these limits
on ourselves definitely makes it...

1089
00:40:09,074 --> 00:40:13,273
Doing things differently from our
usual style makes it feel fresh.

1090
00:40:13,273 --> 00:40:14,278
Yeah.

1091
00:40:14,278 --> 00:40:16,898
It would've been different
if I'd done this alone.

1092
00:40:17,807 --> 00:40:22,034
Wow, our fate was decided
the moment Woo Shik picked Daegu.

1093
00:40:22,034 --> 00:40:25,882
Daegu is basically
my second hometown, isn't it?

1094
00:40:25,882 --> 00:40:27,889
We didn't go to Chungcheong-do Province
this time, right?

1095
00:40:27,889 --> 00:40:28,976
Yeah.

1096
00:40:28,976 --> 00:40:31,842
[Looking back on the places they visited]
Jeolla, Daegu.

1097
00:40:31,842 --> 00:40:34,268
We took a bus from Namwon to Boseong, right?

1098
00:40:34,268 --> 00:40:35,851
Yeah.

1099
00:40:35,851 --> 00:40:37,351
Train.

1100
00:40:37,351 --> 00:40:38,358
Huh?

1101
00:40:38,358 --> 00:40:40,457
Train!

1102
00:40:40,457 --> 00:40:42,763
I can't remember.

1103
00:40:42,763 --> 00:40:45,892
We took the KTX and then the Mugunghwa train.

1104
00:40:45,892 --> 00:40:47,584
Oh, right.

1105
00:40:48,227 --> 00:40:50,633
How did we get to the KTX station?

1106
00:40:50,633 --> 00:40:51,781
[Knows everything]
Taxi.

1107
00:40:51,781 --> 00:40:54,302
Taxi. Ah, that was our first taxi ride, right?

1108
00:40:54,302 --> 00:40:56,016
I even remember how much it cost.

1109
00:40:56,016 --> 00:40:57,787
- 6,300 won.
- 6,300 won. Me too.

1110
00:40:57,787 --> 00:41:00,421
[And thus began...]

1111
00:41:00,421 --> 00:41:03,585
[Travel Quiz on Unplanned Trip]

1112
00:41:03,585 --> 00:41:06,596
What was the name of the jjajang noodles
restaurant in Namwon?

1113
00:41:06,596 --> 00:41:09,076
Chunhyang... Chunhyangru.

1114
00:41:09,076 --> 00:41:10,796
Correct.

1115
00:41:11,557 --> 00:41:13,764
We had raw fish in Boseong.

1116
00:41:13,764 --> 00:41:15,504
We ate striped beakfish.

1117
00:41:15,504 --> 00:41:17,530
Yulpo Beach!

1118
00:41:17,530 --> 00:41:18,631
Yulpo.

1119
00:41:18,631 --> 00:41:20,074
[The next test section is Boseong]

1120
00:41:20,074 --> 00:41:21,492
What was the guesthouse called?

1121
00:41:21,492 --> 00:41:23,739
- Wow.
- Be***.

1122
00:41:23,739 --> 00:41:26,588
It was Be*** something... was it Sunrise Be***?

1123
00:41:26,588 --> 00:41:28,177
Oh, that was the place next door.

1124
00:41:28,177 --> 00:41:29,797
What Be*** was it? Happy Be***!

1125
00:41:29,797 --> 00:41:31,296
- It was just Be***.
- It was just Be***.

1126
00:41:31,296 --> 00:41:33,999
- Oh, it's just Be***.?
- Yeah.

1127
00:41:33,999 --> 00:41:36,112
This one's going to be a bit hard to get right.

1128
00:41:36,112 --> 00:41:37,819
Come on.

1129
00:41:37,819 --> 00:41:41,297
We took a bus to Gwangju.

1130
00:41:41,297 --> 00:41:43,192
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1131
00:41:43,192 --> 00:41:46,467
What were the seat numbers?

1132
00:41:46,467 --> 00:41:48,788
I think it was 25, 26, and 27.

1133
00:41:48,788 --> 00:41:51,074
No way.

1134
00:41:51,074 --> 00:41:53,061
You little punk.

1135
00:41:53,061 --> 00:41:56,734
What was the bus number
we took to Gwangju Airport?

1136
00:41:56,734 --> 00:41:58,130
Number 2.

1137
00:41:58,130 --> 00:41:59,730
Correct.

1138
00:41:59,730 --> 00:42:01,798
Oh, this one's pretty hard.

1139
00:42:01,798 --> 00:42:05,770
- What is it?
- From the Boseong Bus Terminal...

1140
00:42:05,770 --> 00:42:08,550
we took a bus to the Boseong Green Tea Fields.

1141
00:42:08,550 --> 00:42:09,602
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1142
00:42:09,602 --> 00:42:11,184
What was the bus number?

1143
00:42:11,184 --> 00:42:12,434
Number 2-4.

1144
00:42:12,434 --> 00:42:13,836
- Wrong.
- Nope.

1145
00:42:13,836 --> 00:42:15,370
Was it 70-5?

1146
00:42:15,370 --> 00:42:16,511
- 7-5.
- Wrong.

1147
00:42:16,511 --> 00:42:17,535
No.

1148
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:19,754
- 71-5?
- Wrong.

1149
00:42:19,754 --> 00:42:21,781
[The highest wrong-answer rate ever]

1150
00:42:21,781 --> 00:42:24,391
- 76-1.
- Oh, really?

1151
00:42:24,391 --> 00:42:25,953
[Not that one...]

1152
00:42:25,953 --> 00:42:27,412
71-5?

1153
00:42:27,412 --> 00:42:28,589
[Seo Jun gets it right again]

1154
00:42:28,589 --> 00:42:31,639
[The travel quiz makes them lose track of time]
Those memories are still pretty fresh.

1155
00:42:31,639 --> 00:42:33,075
We're in downtown now.

1156
00:42:33,075 --> 00:42:35,231
[Before they know it, they're in Jeju City]

1157
00:42:35,231 --> 00:42:37,044
It's about time...

1158
00:42:37,044 --> 00:42:39,487
- We need to find one now.
- Right.

1159
00:42:40,959 --> 00:42:43,233
Man, with this 100,000 won...

1160
00:42:43,233 --> 00:42:45,570
- Can we make this work?
- Can we?

1161
00:42:45,570 --> 00:42:48,132
[Current balance: 129,200 won]

1162
00:42:48,132 --> 00:42:50,743
Since I can't search it...

1163
00:42:50,743 --> 00:42:54,187
[The late-night walk-in lodging mission begins]

1164
00:42:54,187 --> 00:42:56,205
I'll drop you off... take a look.

1165
00:42:56,205 --> 00:42:57,784
- You're dropping us off?
- Wait...

1166
00:42:57,784 --> 00:42:59,252
First, I'll drop you off in front of the place.

1167
00:42:59,252 --> 00:43:00,784
See how much it costs.

1168
00:43:00,784 --> 00:43:04,384
If it doesn't work,
just hop back on and we'll go.

1169
00:43:05,024 --> 00:43:08,683
[They keep an eye out for a place to stay]

1170
00:43:08,683 --> 00:43:10,242
There's a tourist hotel up ahead.

1171
00:43:10,242 --> 00:43:11,326
Should I stop there first?

1172
00:43:11,326 --> 00:43:14,546
- A hotel? I don't think a hotel will work.
- Where?

1173
00:43:14,546 --> 00:43:17,884
- The tourist hotel?
- There's Na* Motel over there.

1174
00:43:17,884 --> 00:43:20,017
[Their eyes naturally
drift to the motel next door...]

1175
00:43:20,017 --> 00:43:21,591
- San*** Motel.
- San*** Motel?

1176
00:43:21,591 --> 00:43:23,300
Shin*** Motel.

1177
00:43:23,300 --> 00:43:26,967
[Seo Jun and Woo Shik
spot a street full of motels]

1178
00:43:26,967 --> 00:43:29,298
Should we check it out?

1179
00:43:29,298 --> 00:43:30,325
Should we?

1180
00:43:30,325 --> 00:43:32,265
- This way, right? Here?
- Yeah.

1181
00:43:32,265 --> 00:43:34,146
That San*** Motel.

1182
00:43:34,146 --> 00:43:36,544
- Yumi, park here for a second.
- Okay.

1183
00:43:36,544 --> 00:43:39,385
[They stop briefly near the motel]

1184
00:43:39,385 --> 00:43:42,252
- We'll check it out.
- See you in a bit.

1185
00:43:42,252 --> 00:43:45,241
[The lodging scouts get out of the car]

1186
00:43:45,241 --> 00:43:47,738
[The lodging reconnaissance begins]

1187
00:43:48,485 --> 00:43:49,960
[Candidate 1: San***]

1188
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:51,099
- Excuse me,
- Yeah.

1189
00:43:51,099 --> 00:43:53,105
do you have any rooms available?

1190
00:43:54,054 --> 00:43:56,320
Two rooms for three people.

1191
00:43:56,320 --> 00:43:57,409
- Do you have any?
- Yes, we do.

1192
00:43:57,409 --> 00:44:00,262
- How much is it?
- 40,000 won for two people in one room.

1193
00:44:00,262 --> 00:44:03,715
- 35,000 won for one, 40,000 for two?
- Yeah.

1194
00:44:03,715 --> 00:44:06,675
- Can we take a look at the room?
- Yes. Go ahead.

1195
00:44:06,675 --> 00:44:08,395
Rooms 307 and 305.

1196
00:44:08,395 --> 00:44:10,111
[Heading to the third floor to check the rooms]

1197
00:44:10,111 --> 00:44:13,400
Oh, nice vibe. It's classic.

1198
00:44:13,400 --> 00:44:16,119
[The atmosphere passes the test]

1199
00:44:16,119 --> 00:44:19,272
[But will the interior pass too?]

1200
00:44:19,272 --> 00:44:23,218
- Oh, this is nice. Not bad.
- Can I take a look?

1201
00:44:23,218 --> 00:44:26,288
- Actually pretty good.
- Hey, for this price...

1202
00:44:26,288 --> 00:44:27,855
Wow, the bathroom is clean too.

1203
00:44:27,855 --> 00:44:29,741
[Even a clean bathroom with a bathtub]

1204
00:44:29,741 --> 00:44:30,864
I'm good with it.

1205
00:44:30,864 --> 00:44:33,296
[The first candidate already feels promising]
Me too.

1206
00:44:34,035 --> 00:44:36,137
Isn't this a selfie zone?

1207
00:44:36,137 --> 00:44:39,271
[Selfie pose]

1208
00:44:39,271 --> 00:44:42,430
[The lodging's selfie spot wins them over]
Oh, this is nice.

1209
00:44:43,177 --> 00:44:46,681
[After finishing the first inspection...]

1210
00:44:46,681 --> 00:44:48,286
Shin*** Hotel. Let's go.

1211
00:44:48,286 --> 00:44:50,374
[They immediately check the next candidate]

1212
00:44:50,374 --> 00:44:51,793
Hello.

1213
00:44:51,793 --> 00:44:54,024
[Candidate 2: Shin*** Hotel]
Hello.

1214
00:44:54,024 --> 00:44:56,037
Ma'am.

1215
00:44:56,037 --> 00:44:57,777
- Oh, customers are here?
- Yeah.

1216
00:44:57,777 --> 00:44:59,232
Do you happen to have a room available?

1217
00:44:59,232 --> 00:45:02,665
We do have rooms, but...
the boiler isn't working today.

1218
00:45:02,665 --> 00:45:06,232
I see. Then we'll come another time.

1219
00:45:06,232 --> 00:45:09,175
- Thank you.
- Thank you!

1220
00:45:09,175 --> 00:45:12,214
[Candidate 2 is unavailable
due to the boiler issue]

1221
00:45:14,062 --> 00:45:17,009
Hello, sir. Do you have a room?

1222
00:45:17,009 --> 00:45:18,129
Yes, we do.

1223
00:45:18,129 --> 00:45:20,012
By any chance, how much is it?

1224
00:45:20,012 --> 00:45:21,039
40,000 won each.

1225
00:45:21,039 --> 00:45:23,339
- 40,000 won each?
- 40,000 won?

1226
00:45:24,151 --> 00:45:27,942
I think San*** is the one.
Should we have Yumi see it?

1227
00:45:27,942 --> 00:45:30,755
I think this is the only place around here

1228
00:45:30,755 --> 00:45:32,052
- at this price.
- Even to me.

1229
00:45:32,052 --> 00:45:34,597
And it would only cost 75,000 won.

1230
00:45:34,597 --> 00:45:37,609
This place even costs 40,000 won per person.

1231
00:45:37,609 --> 00:45:38,737
[A 5,000 won difference won them over]

1232
00:45:38,737 --> 00:45:40,560
- Right?
- Yeah.

1233
00:45:40,560 --> 00:45:42,198
Should we bring Yumi over?

1234
00:45:42,198 --> 00:45:44,058
Should we let her take a look?

1235
00:45:44,058 --> 00:45:47,552
[To the final decision-maker: Oldest Yumi]

1236
00:45:47,552 --> 00:45:50,065
[Yumi spots the younger brothers]

1237
00:45:50,065 --> 00:45:53,640
- Yumi, want to check out the room condition?
- Why?

1238
00:45:53,640 --> 00:45:55,988
- It looks fine to us.
- Yeah.

1239
00:45:55,988 --> 00:45:58,370
- But it might be uncomfortable for you.
- Me?

1240
00:45:58,370 --> 00:45:59,648
How much is it?

1241
00:45:59,648 --> 00:46:01,788
- 35,000 won.
- Then let's go there.

1242
00:46:01,788 --> 00:46:02,936
[Decision made]
Let's go.

1243
00:46:02,936 --> 00:46:04,977
- Grab your bags.
- Let's grab our bags and go.

1244
00:46:04,977 --> 00:46:06,590
- We checked all three places.
- We checked Shin*** too.

1245
00:46:06,590 --> 00:46:08,389
- You compared them?
- Yeah.

1246
00:46:08,389 --> 00:46:11,042
- So this one's the best?
- Yeah. The best one.

1247
00:46:11,042 --> 00:46:13,067
Oh? This place is cute.

1248
00:46:13,067 --> 00:46:16,584
- Cute. San***.
- Yeah, this place has a vibe.

1249
00:46:16,584 --> 00:46:18,943
[Entering their charming lodging]
Wow, this is really nice.

1250
00:46:18,943 --> 00:46:21,283
- Sir, we'll take two rooms.
- Hello.

1251
00:46:21,283 --> 00:46:22,624
We'll pay 80,000 won.

1252
00:46:22,624 --> 00:46:24,381
- 80,000 won?
- Yes.

1253
00:46:24,381 --> 00:46:27,983
[Now, they just need to get
the remaining 5,000 won in change...]

1254
00:46:27,983 --> 00:46:31,446
Sir, so it's 35,000 won
and 40,000 won per room, right?

1255
00:46:31,446 --> 00:46:34,369
[Trying the total one more time just in case]
One room is 35,000 won.

1256
00:46:34,369 --> 00:46:36,612
He's just leaving.

1257
00:46:37,414 --> 00:46:39,561
- Seo Jun, we need to get 5,000 won back.
- Alright.

1258
00:46:39,561 --> 00:46:41,657
[Nervous]

1259
00:46:41,657 --> 00:46:44,590
These two. Rooms 305 and 306.

1260
00:46:44,590 --> 00:46:45,758
Yes, and...

1261
00:46:45,758 --> 00:46:48,724
then the 5,000 won...

1262
00:46:49,332 --> 00:46:50,859
Did I forget to give you 5,000 won back?

1263
00:46:50,859 --> 00:46:51,885
- Yes.
- Yes.

1264
00:46:51,885 --> 00:46:53,118
Ah, 80,000 won. Right.

1265
00:46:53,118 --> 00:46:54,551
- Right?
- Because it's 80,000 won...

1266
00:46:54,551 --> 00:46:55,818
Yes, that's right.

1267
00:46:55,818 --> 00:46:57,213
[Successfully secured the 5,000 won]

1268
00:46:57,213 --> 00:46:59,474
[Our precious 5,000 won]
Thank you.

1269
00:46:59,474 --> 00:47:02,788
[Expense report: Jeju Lodging -75,000 won,
Balance: 54,200 won]

1270
00:47:02,788 --> 00:47:05,108
Oh, this is nice. Hey, this is really nice.

1271
00:47:05,108 --> 00:47:08,309
[Heading up to the third floor
where the rooms are]

1272
00:47:08,909 --> 00:47:10,825
[Yumi, look at this]

1273
00:47:10,825 --> 00:47:13,511
[Showing off the selfie spot he picked out]

1274
00:47:13,511 --> 00:47:16,707
[Practicing poses]

1275
00:47:16,707 --> 00:47:18,236
Who's staying alone?

1276
00:47:18,236 --> 00:47:19,870
- The person staying alone is here.
- Yes, me.

1277
00:47:19,870 --> 00:47:21,762
- This is your room.
- Yes.

1278
00:47:21,762 --> 00:47:24,264
[Checked in]

1279
00:47:24,264 --> 00:47:26,510
[Clatter]

1280
00:47:26,510 --> 00:47:28,717
[There are even two bottles of water]

1281
00:47:28,717 --> 00:47:30,795
It's very clean.

1282
00:47:30,795 --> 00:47:33,040
We found a good one.

1283
00:47:33,040 --> 00:47:34,623
[Nods]

1284
00:47:34,623 --> 00:47:36,921
I'm satisfied,
considering we found it so suddenly.

1285
00:47:36,921 --> 00:47:41,724
For us, saving even 5,000 won is huge.

1286
00:47:41,724 --> 00:47:45,344
[The 5,000 won that swayed the choice]
So that 5,000 won was actually a big deal.

1287
00:47:45,344 --> 00:47:46,991
It was 5,000 won cheaper.

1288
00:47:46,991 --> 00:47:49,490
- Well, I found that too, actually.
- Oh, really?

1289
00:47:49,490 --> 00:47:51,700
[Time to take credit]
- So you found it as well? - Yeah.

1290
00:47:51,700 --> 00:47:54,194
So if it weren't for me, this trip...

1291
00:47:54,194 --> 00:47:56,334
we wouldn't even be here.

1292
00:47:56,334 --> 00:47:59,792
- You made this whole thing happen?
- Yeah, I kind of want to say that.

1293
00:47:59,792 --> 00:48:01,945
Are there any other rooms
available on the third floor?

1294
00:48:01,945 --> 00:48:05,418
There are more people who might stay,
so I wanted to check.

1295
00:48:06,508 --> 00:48:09,836
[Jeju walk-in lodging mission: Success]

1296
00:48:09,836 --> 00:48:11,974
Hey, we don't even have an alarm right now.

1297
00:48:11,974 --> 00:48:14,398
[Wait, how are we supposed to wake up?]
Don't we have a clock?

1298
00:48:14,398 --> 00:48:16,263
Let's ask the owner to wake us up.

1299
00:48:16,263 --> 00:48:17,973
[Creative]
The owner?

1300
00:48:17,973 --> 00:48:20,333
I don't think he'll wake up either.

1301
00:48:21,013 --> 00:48:22,687
Let me see how much we have left.

1302
00:48:22,687 --> 00:48:24,490
We still have quite a bit left.

1303
00:48:24,490 --> 00:48:26,960
- We can probably take a taxi tomorrow.
- Yeah.

1304
00:48:26,960 --> 00:48:28,362
[Deeply moved]

1305
00:48:28,362 --> 00:48:30,541
- How much is left?
- Because...

1306
00:48:30,541 --> 00:48:33,301
[As she opens the wallet]

1307
00:48:33,301 --> 00:48:35,385
- Huh? This is all we've got, right?
- Yeah.

1308
00:48:35,385 --> 00:48:37,077
- Huh?
- Hun?

1309
00:48:38,382 --> 00:48:41,408
[She starts counting from the 1,000 won bills]
One, two, three, four...

1310
00:48:43,942 --> 00:48:46,546
It's over 40,000 won. Over 50,000 won.

1311
00:48:46,546 --> 00:48:49,321
[Their entire fortune
fluttering around 54,200 won]

1312
00:48:49,321 --> 00:48:51,680
We saved 5,000 won.

1313
00:48:51,680 --> 00:48:56,609
When we went to Gimpo,
I took the A*M Black, and it cost 56,000 won.

1314
00:48:56,609 --> 00:49:01,176
Then if we just take a regular taxi,
wouldn't it be cheaper?

1315
00:49:01,176 --> 00:49:04,483
[Dreaming of taking a taxi in Gimpo tomorrow]
We can actually afford a taxi. A regular taxi.

1316
00:49:04,483 --> 00:49:05,923
- Bye!
- Yeah.

1317
00:49:05,923 --> 00:49:08,029
- Take a rest.
- Get some rest.

1318
00:49:08,029 --> 00:49:10,803
[For the early 6 AM checkout]

1319
00:49:10,803 --> 00:49:14,237
[They try to get some sleep early]

1320
00:49:14,237 --> 00:49:15,565
I'm going to shower tomorrow.

1321
00:49:15,565 --> 00:49:19,166
No, we're leaving at six.
I'm not gonna take a shower.

1322
00:49:19,166 --> 00:49:22,136
[The younger guys' room lights go out too]

1323
00:49:22,136 --> 00:49:26,607
[The night in Jeju grows deeper]

1324
00:49:29,154 --> 00:49:32,567
[The long-awaited final day of the trip]

1325
00:49:32,567 --> 00:49:36,330
[The darkness hasn't lifted yet]

1326
00:49:37,441 --> 00:49:40,861
[But the workers of the sea
have already started their day]

1327
00:49:40,861 --> 00:49:44,383
[And flights have already begun operating]

1328
00:49:44,383 --> 00:49:47,274
[First one awake: Yumi]

1329
00:49:47,274 --> 00:49:50,978
[Stretching her back nice and long]

1330
00:49:50,978 --> 00:49:53,790
[She packs up after 5 nights and 6 days]

1331
00:49:55,400 --> 00:49:58,049
[The beloved padded jacket comes down]

1332
00:49:58,049 --> 00:50:00,857
[The pajamas she's worn
since day two of the trip]

1333
00:50:00,857 --> 00:50:03,880
[Are carefully rolled up]

1334
00:50:03,880 --> 00:50:06,402
[And tucked into the bag]

1335
00:50:06,402 --> 00:50:09,040
[Meanwhile, the younger guys are awake too]

1336
00:50:09,040 --> 00:50:11,246
There's no hair dryer here.

1337
00:50:11,873 --> 00:50:13,148
[It's right here though?]
Here.

1338
00:50:13,148 --> 00:50:14,806
Oh, darn it.

1339
00:50:16,066 --> 00:50:18,592
[Slide]

1340
00:50:18,592 --> 00:50:21,245
[Why isn't it working?]

1341
00:50:21,245 --> 00:50:24,501
[Outlet hunting in the dark]

1342
00:50:24,501 --> 00:50:27,041
[Eventually gives up...]

1343
00:50:27,041 --> 00:50:29,931
[6:00 AM, meeting time]

1344
00:50:29,931 --> 00:50:32,085
- Hello.
- Hello.

1345
00:50:32,085 --> 00:50:33,289
[Yumi is all ready]

1346
00:50:33,289 --> 00:50:34,508
Did you sleep well?

1347
00:50:34,508 --> 00:50:35,929
Water.

1348
00:50:35,929 --> 00:50:37,611
[Habitually grabbing water]

1349
00:50:37,611 --> 00:50:40,248
[Woo Shik is ready too]

1350
00:50:40,248 --> 00:50:43,971
[And Seo Jun is ready to head out as well]

1351
00:50:43,971 --> 00:50:48,275
[Loaded up with bags]

1352
00:50:48,275 --> 00:50:50,440
[The long-awaited selfie zone
on the way downstairs]

1353
00:50:50,440 --> 00:50:52,445
Let's take one together.

1354
00:50:53,383 --> 00:50:56,328
[Taking a commemorative photo
with the crew's phone]

1355
00:50:56,328 --> 00:50:58,061
[Hahaha]

1356
00:50:58,061 --> 00:51:00,141
- We're leaving.
- We're leaving.

1357
00:51:02,883 --> 00:51:04,064
We had a great stay.

1358
00:51:04,064 --> 00:51:05,426
- Yes, thank you.
- Thank you.

1359
00:51:05,426 --> 00:51:07,293
- Did you get some sleep?
- Yes.

1360
00:51:07,293 --> 00:51:09,179
Yes, thank you.

1361
00:51:09,179 --> 00:51:11,246
[They leave the lodging
with the owner's farewell]

1362
00:51:11,246 --> 00:51:12,633
- Oh, dear.
- Oh, my.

1363
00:51:12,633 --> 00:51:13,928
[The long-coat man appears in the distance]

1364
00:51:13,928 --> 00:51:15,769
A street musician.

1365
00:51:15,769 --> 00:51:17,184
You look like a street musician.

1366
00:51:17,184 --> 00:51:19,710
A street musician...

1367
00:51:19,710 --> 00:51:21,478
All he needs is a guitar.

1368
00:51:21,478 --> 00:51:22,852
Now let's swap...

1369
00:51:22,852 --> 00:51:25,165
- Should we change clothes now?
- Yeah.

1370
00:51:25,165 --> 00:51:27,408
[Grunts]

1371
00:51:27,408 --> 00:51:30,310
[Woo Shik's coat reunites with its owner]

1372
00:51:30,310 --> 00:51:31,990
Okay.

1373
00:51:31,990 --> 00:51:33,404
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1374
00:51:33,404 --> 00:51:34,618
[Let's head back to Seoul]

1375
00:51:34,618 --> 00:51:36,604
Oh, it's raining.

1376
00:51:36,604 --> 00:51:39,793
[They quickly load the luggage
as the raindrops get heavier]

1377
00:51:39,793 --> 00:51:41,520
Oh, it's raining. It's raining.

1378
00:51:41,520 --> 00:51:44,334
[And quickly hop in themselves]
It's raining.

1379
00:51:44,334 --> 00:51:46,808
- To Jeju International Airport, right?
- Yeah.

1380
00:51:46,808 --> 00:51:48,502
International Airport.

1381
00:51:48,502 --> 00:51:51,094
Wow, it really feels like we just got here.

1382
00:51:51,094 --> 00:51:54,274
It looks exactly the same as yesterday.
The view, I mean.

1383
00:51:55,016 --> 00:51:58,351
[Surprisingly, it's a different day]

1384
00:51:58,351 --> 00:52:01,654
If we were out exploring right now...

1385
00:52:01,654 --> 00:52:02,808
Just come here, right?

1386
00:52:02,808 --> 00:52:05,415
- Watch the sunrise.
- Right.

1387
00:52:06,068 --> 00:52:07,914
Drive along the coastal road.

1388
00:52:07,914 --> 00:52:10,175
Grab some breakfast.

1389
00:52:10,175 --> 00:52:12,533
We're heading up there now, right?

1390
00:52:12,533 --> 00:52:15,123
- Departures...
- Departures, general boarding.

1391
00:52:16,172 --> 00:52:18,384
Here are the directors. Over there.

1392
00:52:18,384 --> 00:52:21,303
[6:20 AM, arrive at the airport]

1393
00:52:21,303 --> 00:52:25,096
[After the long sea-crossing journey
from Gwangju to Wando to Jeju]

1394
00:52:25,096 --> 00:52:28,682
[They return the benefit vehicle to the crew]

1395
00:52:28,682 --> 00:52:31,538
[And head inside the airport]

1396
00:52:31,538 --> 00:52:33,749
Lot*eria looks good.

1397
00:52:34,407 --> 00:52:38,188
I'm hungry, cold, and tired.

1398
00:52:38,188 --> 00:52:40,487
This is what travel is all about.

1399
00:52:40,487 --> 00:52:41,722
The triple combo.

1400
00:52:41,722 --> 00:52:44,358
[The triple combo only
true travelers experience]

1401
00:52:44,358 --> 00:52:47,895
[6:57 AM, boarding the plane]

1402
00:52:47,895 --> 00:52:49,475
We'll guide you further inside.

1403
00:52:49,475 --> 00:52:52,481
- Further in?
- Yes, this way.

1404
00:52:53,194 --> 00:52:57,403
[As they keep moving farther into the plane]

1405
00:52:57,403 --> 00:52:59,606
[The trio arrives at their seats]

1406
00:52:59,606 --> 00:53:01,585
We're on.

1407
00:53:01,585 --> 00:53:03,536
We're going back to Seoul.

1408
00:53:04,230 --> 00:53:07,427
Wow, we ended up taking a plane in the end.

1409
00:53:07,427 --> 00:53:08,881
Should we get one last shot?

1410
00:53:08,881 --> 00:53:09,975
[Peace sign]

1411
00:53:09,975 --> 00:53:13,867
[A camcorder selfie to commemorate
boarding the plane]

1412
00:53:13,867 --> 00:53:16,607
[The camera sways along with
their excited hearts]

1413
00:53:16,607 --> 00:53:18,873
<i>Please return your seat back
to the upright position</i>

1414
00:53:18,873 --> 00:53:20,601
<i>and fold away your tray tables.</i>

1415
00:53:20,601 --> 00:53:23,626
Huh? The sun's up! The sun's up!

1416
00:53:23,626 --> 00:53:25,466
[Turns quickly]

1417
00:53:25,466 --> 00:53:28,009
[Oh!]

1418
00:53:28,684 --> 00:53:33,038
[Meanwhile, the sun gently rises]

1419
00:53:34,305 --> 00:53:38,646
[A Jeju trip viewed through the window,
from sunset to sunrise]

1420
00:53:38,646 --> 00:53:41,618
[7:10 AM, plane takes off]

1421
00:53:41,618 --> 00:53:44,572
[Leaving the sea below
and getting closer to the sun]

1422
00:53:45,651 --> 00:53:48,182
[Moving forward through the fog]

1423
00:53:49,164 --> 00:53:54,451
[Fluffy clouds you just want to jump onto!]

1424
00:53:54,451 --> 00:53:58,669
[Meanwhile, all three have fallen fast asleep]

1425
00:53:58,669 --> 00:53:59,823
[Nod]

1426
00:53:59,823 --> 00:54:01,629
[Hello]

1427
00:54:03,522 --> 00:54:07,315
[While Woo Shik greets the air]

1428
00:54:07,315 --> 00:54:09,513
[Ding]

1429
00:54:09,513 --> 00:54:13,536
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
our aircraft will be landing shortly.</i>

1430
00:54:13,536 --> 00:54:17,349
[8:10 AM, arrive at Gimpo Airport]
<i>Please fasten your seat belts. Thank you.</i>

1431
00:54:17,349 --> 00:54:19,850
That was the shortest flight ever.

1432
00:54:19,850 --> 00:54:22,102
[After a nap, they're already there]
The shortest flight ever.

1433
00:54:22,102 --> 00:54:24,308
Shall we start getting ready to go?

1434
00:54:25,081 --> 00:54:27,864
[Yumi jumps right up]

1435
00:54:27,864 --> 00:54:30,379
[And doesn't forget her precious plastic bag]

1436
00:54:30,379 --> 00:54:32,348
Wow, we're in Seoul.

1437
00:54:32,348 --> 00:54:35,303
We somehow made it here.

1438
00:54:35,303 --> 00:54:38,665
[The trio has come a long way]
Wando, then Jeju, then Gimpo.

1439
00:54:38,665 --> 00:54:40,968
Doesn't it almost feel like
we traveled overseas?

1440
00:54:40,968 --> 00:54:42,255
Pretty much.

1441
00:54:42,255 --> 00:54:45,008
Feels like I've been away for a month.

1442
00:54:45,008 --> 00:54:46,635
Whoa, it's cold.

1443
00:54:46,635 --> 00:54:48,618
Oh, it's cold. Seoul is cold.

1444
00:54:48,618 --> 00:54:50,011
[Seoul's bitter cold welcomes them]

1445
00:54:50,011 --> 00:54:51,331
Seoul is the coldest.

1446
00:54:51,331 --> 00:54:52,846
Let's get a taxi. Ah, there it is.

1447
00:54:52,846 --> 00:54:54,725
Guys, we have to cross over there.

1448
00:54:54,725 --> 00:54:57,260
- We need to cross and get one there.
- Should we cross?

1449
00:54:57,260 --> 00:54:59,507
- Let's cross.
- Should we cross?

1450
00:54:59,507 --> 00:55:02,596
[They decide to head to the taxi stand
across the street first]

1451
00:55:02,596 --> 00:55:05,124
[Current balance: 54,200 won]

1452
00:55:05,124 --> 00:55:08,504
[The key question is
whether they'll have enough money]

1453
00:55:08,504 --> 00:55:11,455
Huh? Should we go over there?
There's a large taxi.

1454
00:55:11,455 --> 00:55:12,523
[They're even eyeing
the more spacious large taxi]

1455
00:55:12,523 --> 00:55:14,988
- A jumbo taxi is probably expensive.
- There's a large one.

1456
00:55:14,988 --> 00:55:16,497
I think it'll be expensive.

1457
00:55:16,497 --> 00:55:18,260
That's expensive.

1458
00:55:18,260 --> 00:55:20,748
[Then they spot the taxi fare chart]

1459
00:55:20,748 --> 00:55:22,189
7,000 won.

1460
00:55:22,189 --> 00:55:24,767
What? 200 won every 36 seconds?

1461
00:55:24,767 --> 00:55:27,054
From here to Nonhyeon-dong...

1462
00:55:27,054 --> 00:55:29,527
[The treasurer immediately
starts doing the math]

1463
00:55:29,527 --> 00:55:31,756
Hey, it's enough. Plenty, I think.

1464
00:55:31,756 --> 00:55:33,813
[As the youngest starts to worry]
What if it isn't enough?

1465
00:55:33,813 --> 00:55:35,851
Excuse me, which one of you is the driver?

1466
00:55:35,851 --> 00:55:37,534
[The rookie gets nervous,
so the Public Liaison Officer steps in]

1467
00:55:37,534 --> 00:55:39,806
How much would it cost to get to Nonhyeon-dong?

1468
00:55:39,806 --> 00:55:41,581
- It'll be under 50,000 won.
- Really?

1469
00:55:41,581 --> 00:55:43,208
- Yeah.
- Then we'll take this one.

1470
00:55:43,208 --> 00:55:44,520
- Hop in, then.
- Oh, my.

1471
00:55:44,520 --> 00:55:46,635
[Street casting, before they knew it]
Oh wow, nice.

1472
00:55:46,635 --> 00:55:48,972
Watch your head.

1473
00:55:48,972 --> 00:55:51,794
Wow, we're really going.

1474
00:55:51,794 --> 00:55:56,319
[They set off, amazed to be heading into Seoul]

1475
00:55:56,319 --> 00:55:58,179
Wow, we got a nice ride.

1476
00:55:58,179 --> 00:56:00,083
- Seriously.
- Seriously...

1477
00:56:00,083 --> 00:56:01,736
I thought this would be pretty expensive.

1478
00:56:01,736 --> 00:56:03,848
But we saved so much...

1479
00:56:03,848 --> 00:56:06,492
- on lodging yesterday.
- Exactly.

1480
00:56:06,492 --> 00:56:08,029
Already 10,000 won.

1481
00:56:08,029 --> 00:56:10,399
[Still, they keep glancing at the meter...]

1482
00:56:10,399 --> 00:56:12,259
[Current time: 9:18 AM]
- Well... - Ready...

1483
00:56:12,259 --> 00:56:14,639
Since it's 200 won every 36 seconds.

1484
00:56:14,639 --> 00:56:17,533
[Calculating...]

1485
00:56:17,533 --> 00:56:18,814
35 minutes.

1486
00:56:18,814 --> 00:56:20,130
[About 35 minutes left to the Egg headquarters]

1487
00:56:20,130 --> 00:56:22,166
[Relieved for now]
It's enough.

1488
00:56:22,166 --> 00:56:24,929
It feels like we've come
somewhere else again. A big city.

1489
00:56:24,929 --> 00:56:27,785
How long has it been
since you've been to Seoul?

1490
00:56:27,785 --> 00:56:29,998
Has it only been a week?

1491
00:56:31,020 --> 00:56:33,604
- It feels like it's been a month.
- Yeah, me too.

1492
00:56:33,604 --> 00:56:34,898
- What if...
- Yeah.

1493
00:56:34,898 --> 00:56:39,637
From the very beginning,
what if we had started in Jeju?

1494
00:56:39,637 --> 00:56:42,197
We probably would've taken a ferry to Wando.

1495
00:56:42,197 --> 00:56:44,604
- I don't think that would've been bad either.
- That would've been fun too.

1496
00:56:44,604 --> 00:56:46,365
If we'd just traveled straight up,

1497
00:56:46,365 --> 00:56:48,671
it actually might've been easier
if we'd won the phone.

1498
00:56:48,671 --> 00:56:50,849
We really went all over the place.

1499
00:56:50,849 --> 00:56:52,044
Yeah.

1500
00:56:52,676 --> 00:56:55,432
It feels like we only picked
the hardest routes.

1501
00:56:55,432 --> 00:56:59,270
We even went down to Boseong,
up to Gwangju, then back down to Wando.

1502
00:56:59,270 --> 00:57:02,536
- It's a weird route.
- It's weird.

1503
00:57:02,536 --> 00:57:04,811
We're going to calculate
how many kilometers we traveled.

1504
00:57:04,811 --> 00:57:07,085
- Oh, I'm really curious.
- I'm really curious.

1505
00:57:07,085 --> 00:57:08,722
[5-night, 6-day travel route:
Final final version]

1506
00:57:08,722 --> 00:57:10,599
[Hakdong to Seoul: 7 km]
[Seoul to Dongdaegu: 300 km]

1507
00:57:10,599 --> 00:57:13,292
[Dongdaegu to Namwon: 110 km]
[Namwon to Boseong: 140 km]

1508
00:57:13,292 --> 00:57:15,920
[Boseong to Gwangju: 70 km] [SSangchon
to Wando: 150 km] [Wando to Jeju: 100 km]

1509
00:57:15,920 --> 00:57:17,703
[Jeju to Gimpo: 450 km]
[Gimpo to Hakdong: 25 km]

1510
00:57:17,703 --> 00:57:21,214
[Total travel distance: 1,350 km]

1511
00:57:21,214 --> 00:57:24,121
Yumi, can I have one of those mint candies?

1512
00:57:24,121 --> 00:57:25,521
- Mint candy?
- Yeah.

1513
00:57:25,521 --> 00:57:27,061
Now...

1514
00:57:27,061 --> 00:57:28,585
[Shaking]

1515
00:57:29,183 --> 00:57:31,212
It'd be amazing if there were three left.

1516
00:57:31,212 --> 00:57:33,158
Oh, there are exactly three left.

1517
00:57:33,158 --> 00:57:34,983
Wow!

1518
00:57:34,983 --> 00:57:37,057
Please film this.

1519
00:57:37,687 --> 00:57:39,470
[Precious]
The mint candy we bought.

1520
00:57:39,470 --> 00:57:41,216
We finished it all.

1521
00:57:41,216 --> 00:57:42,333
We really finished every last piece.

1522
00:57:42,333 --> 00:57:44,543
- Was that bought at the beginning?
- Yeah.

1523
00:57:44,543 --> 00:57:47,126
I don't remember exactly when,
but we bought it at the beginning.

1524
00:57:47,126 --> 00:57:49,543
[Quick quiz time]
Guess where we bought it?

1525
00:57:49,543 --> 00:57:52,029
[Where did they buy the mint candy?]

1526
00:57:52,029 --> 00:57:53,456
Boseong Bus Terminal.

1527
00:57:53,456 --> 00:57:55,718
No, was it Suncheon Station?

1528
00:57:55,718 --> 00:57:56,682
[Tilts head]

1529
00:57:56,682 --> 00:57:58,350
- Nope.
- That's where we had hamburgers

1530
00:57:58,350 --> 00:58:00,729
- and sandwiches.
- Yeah, that station.

1531
00:58:00,729 --> 00:58:01,872
Namwon Station.

1532
00:58:01,872 --> 00:58:04,510
[Mint candy purchase location: Namwon Station]

1533
00:58:04,510 --> 00:58:07,674
Someone was eating ramyeon there.

1534
00:58:07,674 --> 00:58:08,858
S** Jjamppong.

1535
00:58:08,858 --> 00:58:11,837
[Proud smile]

1536
00:58:11,837 --> 00:58:14,831
Wow, but Daegu is already a blur.

1537
00:58:14,831 --> 00:58:16,488
[Feels like a past life]
- Already. - Yeah.

1538
00:58:16,488 --> 00:58:18,356
Oh, wait. Then let me give you a quiz.

1539
00:58:18,356 --> 00:58:21,218
[Travel Quiz on Unplanned Trip]
[Daegu Edition]

1540
00:58:21,934 --> 00:58:24,072
What was the name of the first lodging

1541
00:58:24,072 --> 00:58:27,037
we failed to get into after arriving in Daegu?

1542
00:58:27,037 --> 00:58:28,982
That was... Mu** Inn.

1543
00:58:28,982 --> 00:58:30,999
- Daegu?
- Yeah, that's right.

1544
00:58:30,999 --> 00:58:32,298
Right.

1545
00:58:32,298 --> 00:58:36,399
What was the name of the place
we eventually checked into?

1546
00:58:36,399 --> 00:58:38,947
- Hotel Fi**d.
- Hotel Fi**d.

1547
00:58:40,085 --> 00:58:42,152
How much was one night there?

1548
00:58:42,152 --> 00:58:43,624
- 60,000 won.
- 60,000 won.

1549
00:58:43,624 --> 00:58:46,271
- You're exactly right.
- Try another one.

1550
00:58:46,271 --> 00:58:50,505
What was the name of the market
where we had dinner in Daegu?

1551
00:58:51,145 --> 00:58:53,673
Well...

1552
00:58:53,673 --> 00:58:55,334
- Ah...
- Yeongtong Market!

1553
00:58:55,334 --> 00:58:57,180
- No.
- Wrong!

1554
00:58:57,180 --> 00:58:59,281
Ah, it was the Chicken Gizzard Alley,

1555
00:58:59,281 --> 00:59:01,058
Jangteo... no, that's not it.

1556
00:59:01,058 --> 00:59:03,550
- It was two syllables.
- Two syllables... something Market.

1557
00:59:03,550 --> 00:59:06,531
- Wow, Daegu's already fading from memory.
- I can't remember Daegu at all.

1558
00:59:06,531 --> 00:59:08,901
[The correct answer is Pyeonghwa Market]
Oh, right! Pyeonghwa Market.

1559
00:59:08,901 --> 00:59:11,004
Ah, I got half of it right.

1560
00:59:11,004 --> 00:59:14,224
If we did this a month later,
I'd remember nothing.

1561
00:59:14,224 --> 00:59:16,204
As expected, traffic gets bad
once we reach Gangnam.

1562
00:59:16,204 --> 00:59:18,444
[Sneak peek]

1563
00:59:18,444 --> 00:59:20,524
It's 35,000 won now.

1564
00:59:20,524 --> 00:59:22,717
- Is the fare showing?
- Yeah, down there.

1565
00:59:22,717 --> 00:59:24,966
[Once the quiz show ends,
the taxi fare starts becoming a concern]

1566
00:59:24,966 --> 00:59:26,945
Did we have 52,000 won left?

1567
00:59:26,945 --> 00:59:28,516
54,000 won.

1568
00:59:28,516 --> 00:59:30,758
Even if it doesn't work out,
I think it'll be close enough to walk.

1569
00:59:30,758 --> 00:59:32,857
Then let's ask to get dropped off right there.

1570
00:59:32,857 --> 00:59:36,239
[While the trio plans a possible early exit...]

1571
00:59:36,239 --> 00:59:40,102
[At the same time, at Egg headquarters...]

1572
00:59:40,102 --> 00:59:43,428
[Return livestream setup complete]

1573
00:59:43,428 --> 00:59:46,162
[Congratulations on your safe return]
[Ready to welcome the trio]

1574
00:59:46,162 --> 00:59:48,496
- We're almost there.
- Then...

1575
00:59:48,496 --> 00:59:50,244
[So what will the taxi fare be?]
How much is it?

1576
00:59:50,244 --> 00:59:53,702
- The price is fine.
- It is 39,600 won.

1577
00:59:53,702 --> 00:59:56,143
[Totally affordable
with the remaining 54,200 won]

1578
00:59:56,143 --> 00:59:57,471
[The taxi keeps rolling]

1579
00:59:57,471 --> 00:59:59,351
One minute until arrival.

1580
00:59:59,958 --> 01:00:02,899
- We're here.
- One minute until arrival.

1581
01:00:02,899 --> 01:00:05,076
We'll have money left.

1582
01:00:05,076 --> 01:00:06,970
You traveled for 120 hours.

1583
01:00:06,970 --> 01:00:08,700
- Wow!
- Wow!

1584
01:00:08,700 --> 01:00:10,633
We really traveled...

1585
01:00:10,633 --> 01:00:12,639
to the very end.

1586
01:00:12,639 --> 01:00:15,196
We really traveled to our heart's content.

1587
01:00:15,196 --> 01:00:18,256
Wow, Torong!

1588
01:00:18,256 --> 01:00:20,692
[Torong, hi]

1589
01:00:20,692 --> 01:00:23,154
[The trio is smiling at something?]
Oh, what is that?

1590
01:00:23,154 --> 01:00:25,554
- I'll give you 45,000 won.
- Oh, it came out to exactly 45,000 won.

1591
01:00:25,554 --> 01:00:27,217
[First, they settle the bill]

1592
01:00:27,217 --> 01:00:29,930
[A warm welcome for the trio?]

1593
01:00:29,930 --> 01:00:31,741
[A gentlemanly greeting]

1594
01:00:31,741 --> 01:00:35,279
[It's simple, but welcome back]

1595
01:00:35,279 --> 01:00:39,399
- Thank you.
- Congratulations on your safe return!

1596
01:00:39,399 --> 01:00:41,910
Aloha.

1597
01:00:41,910 --> 01:00:45,200
- Are we in Hawaii?
- You guys are so cool!

1598
01:00:45,200 --> 01:00:47,600
It smells nice.

1599
01:00:47,600 --> 01:00:49,700
Let's take a commemorative photo.

1600
01:00:49,700 --> 01:00:52,201
[To commemorate their safe arrival]
One, two, three!

1601
01:00:52,201 --> 01:00:53,574
One more shot, please.

1602
01:00:53,574 --> 01:00:56,979
[And after taking a photo]

1603
01:00:56,979 --> 01:00:59,912
[Their 5-night, 6-day journey comes to an end]

1604
01:00:59,912 --> 01:01:03,225
Thank you for all your hard work.
We'll start the livestream right away.

1605
01:01:03,225 --> 01:01:04,991
[The really, really final rule]

1606
01:01:04,991 --> 01:01:09,060
[5. The trip officially ends
when they go live here again on March 1]

1607
01:01:09,060 --> 01:01:11,152
[Unplanned Trip Safe Return Live]

1608
01:01:11,152 --> 01:01:13,068
[Live ON]

1609
01:01:14,512 --> 01:01:15,695
Wait a second.

1610
01:01:15,695 --> 01:01:18,341
[While Na PD greets the subscribers]
They're... hello!

1611
01:01:18,341 --> 01:01:19,729
Hello!

1612
01:01:19,729 --> 01:01:23,215
[The trio waits outside]
Let's go in and do the same pose one by one.

1613
01:01:23,849 --> 01:01:26,283
Your smile level is only about
2% or 5% right now.

1614
01:01:26,283 --> 01:01:28,073
[Their energy is almost completely drained]

1615
01:01:28,073 --> 01:01:29,452
It's going up.

1616
01:01:29,452 --> 01:01:31,332
What percentage?

1617
01:01:31,975 --> 01:01:33,963
Oh, they're telling us to come in.

1618
01:01:33,963 --> 01:01:37,546
[The final moment of the trip
has finally arrived]

1619
01:01:37,546 --> 01:01:39,485
- Should I go first?
- Yumi, you go to the inside.

1620
01:01:39,485 --> 01:01:43,151
- Hello.
- Ah, our proud Unplanned Trip team.

1621
01:01:43,151 --> 01:01:45,691
They're coming in right now.

1622
01:01:45,691 --> 01:01:47,658
Hello.

1623
01:01:48,331 --> 01:01:50,336
Oh, here? Am I sitting here?

1624
01:01:50,336 --> 01:01:53,059
There are no assigned seats. Just sit wherever.

1625
01:01:54,915 --> 01:01:56,987
Oh my God.

1626
01:01:56,987 --> 01:01:58,887
Woo Shik, sit down.

1627
01:01:59,501 --> 01:02:01,746
[They're here! Great job! You made it]
- Hello. - First of all,

1628
01:02:01,746 --> 01:02:03,839
let us greet the subscribers
and let them know we made it back safely.

1629
01:02:03,839 --> 01:02:04,959
We're back safely.

1630
01:02:04,959 --> 01:02:07,106
- We're back safely!
- We're back safely!

1631
01:02:09,254 --> 01:02:13,030
There's a comment saying,
"Why do you all look so much older?"

1632
01:02:13,030 --> 01:02:15,603
[The trio who started out
so fresh and adorable]

1633
01:02:16,536 --> 01:02:20,522
[Must have made too many memories
over the past 5 nights and 6 days]

1634
01:02:20,522 --> 01:02:22,701
I look like a ghost, don't I?
My hair looks ghostly.

1635
01:02:22,701 --> 01:02:24,455
[Only now checking how they look on camera]
First, let's each...

1636
01:02:24,455 --> 01:02:26,354
say hello one by one.

1637
01:02:26,354 --> 01:02:28,542
Let's start with Seo Jun telling
everyone we made it back safely.

1638
01:02:28,542 --> 01:02:31,495
Yes, my heart is still young,

1639
01:02:31,495 --> 01:02:33,913
but I learned that my body isn't.

1640
01:02:33,913 --> 01:02:37,317
- I'm Park Seo Jun.
- Yes, Seo Jun made it back safely.

1641
01:02:37,317 --> 01:02:40,357
Yeah, five, five nights...
how many days was it?

1642
01:02:40,357 --> 01:02:43,921
After an amazing 5-night, 6-day trip
without a single stop,

1643
01:02:43,921 --> 01:02:46,960
I'm Choi Woo Shik, and I'm back. Hello.

1644
01:02:46,960 --> 01:02:48,968
[Woo Shik: A bit of a blur, but a great trip]
And Woo Shik is here.

1645
01:02:48,968 --> 01:02:52,837
- And Yumi as well.
- Hello, for the past 5 nights and 6 days...

1646
01:02:52,837 --> 01:02:54,598
I had a great time...

1647
01:02:54,598 --> 01:02:57,141
I'm Jung Yumi, back
from a trip with my friends.

1648
01:02:57,141 --> 01:02:58,974
[Jung Yumi, Suddenly nervous because it's live]
And that's Yumi.

1649
01:02:58,974 --> 01:03:00,587
[Return livestream roll call complete]

1650
01:03:00,587 --> 01:03:01,841
Yes, they made it back safely.

1651
01:03:01,841 --> 01:03:03,688
- Though they don't look very happy.
- What happened to my appearance?

1652
01:03:03,688 --> 01:03:05,474
- Is this right?
- Isn't that funny?

1653
01:03:05,474 --> 01:03:08,694
Is this Interstellar?
Why do you look like that?

1654
01:03:08,694 --> 01:03:12,375
You look like you've traveled 500 million
light-years or something.

1655
01:03:12,375 --> 01:03:14,345
Still, you had fun, right?

1656
01:03:14,345 --> 01:03:17,257
- Oh, it was so much fun.
- Yes!

1657
01:03:17,257 --> 01:03:19,164
[Memories flashing by like a montage...]
Aren't you...

1658
01:03:19,164 --> 01:03:21,188
aren't you answering with a bit
too little enthusiasm?

1659
01:03:21,188 --> 01:03:22,662
It really was fun.

1660
01:03:22,662 --> 01:03:24,194
[Absolutely!]

1661
01:03:24,194 --> 01:03:26,693
First, I think we're going to need

1662
01:03:26,693 --> 01:03:30,190
- Yeah.
- some explanations for these outfits.

1663
01:03:30,190 --> 01:03:32,985
First, this and this

1664
01:03:32,985 --> 01:03:35,938
- are the same as when we left.
- These are the clothes she left in.

1665
01:03:35,938 --> 01:03:37,010
And...

1666
01:03:37,010 --> 01:03:40,380
Sorry, but is it okay for an actress
to wear the same clothes for six days?

1667
01:03:40,380 --> 01:03:43,859
But I don't really sweat,
so I think it was okay.

1668
01:03:43,859 --> 01:03:45,809
- That's right.
- Because it wasn't hot.

1669
01:03:45,809 --> 01:03:49,425
- You're pretty easygoing.
- Yeah, fortunately.

1670
01:03:49,425 --> 01:03:51,702
Mr. Choi Woo Shik,
please explain your outfit as well.

1671
01:03:51,702 --> 01:03:55,861
Uh... well, it's exactly
what I was wearing back then.

1672
01:03:55,861 --> 01:04:01,641
I think these pants have accumulated
a lot of memories.

1673
01:04:01,641 --> 01:04:02,794
It's a little bit...

1674
01:04:02,794 --> 01:04:04,429
These are the pants that traveled
all around the country, right?

1675
01:04:04,429 --> 01:04:05,675
Yes, yes.

1676
01:04:05,675 --> 01:04:08,449
I went in with this whole
"man of autumn" concept, and...

1677
01:04:08,449 --> 01:04:10,538
- Yes.
- Well...

1678
01:04:10,538 --> 01:04:13,091
ended up being the man
of autumn the entire trip.

1679
01:04:13,091 --> 01:04:15,760
It felt like he was in autumn mode
for all six days.

1680
01:04:15,760 --> 01:04:17,762
Seo Jun, please explain your outfit...

1681
01:04:17,762 --> 01:04:20,063
Let me explain my OOTD today.

1682
01:04:20,063 --> 01:04:21,621
- Yeah.
- Nice.

1683
01:04:22,556 --> 01:04:24,663
First, if I take this off...

1684
01:04:24,663 --> 01:04:27,437
Yep, that's the same outfit he left in.

1685
01:04:27,437 --> 01:04:30,163
- This is not the show from when we left.
- Yeah.

1686
01:04:30,163 --> 01:04:32,682
Actually, if they just
take off the flower lei...

1687
01:04:32,682 --> 01:04:34,642
it'd look exactly like
when they were dragged away.

1688
01:04:34,642 --> 01:04:36,662
Feels like five days ago, right?

1689
01:04:37,563 --> 01:04:40,173
Now, I can't go into detail
because of spoilers,

1690
01:04:40,173 --> 01:04:42,465
but I can at least say this much.

1691
01:04:42,465 --> 01:04:45,871
The next segment is...
"What's in the Shopping Bag?"

1692
01:04:46,518 --> 01:04:48,818
Shall we take a look at the shopping bag,
starting with this one?

1693
01:04:48,818 --> 01:04:50,439
- What's inside?
- I'm not sure if I can...

1694
01:04:50,439 --> 01:04:51,949
even call it a shopping bag.

1695
01:04:51,949 --> 01:04:53,949
There's this plastic bag, and this too...

1696
01:04:53,949 --> 01:04:55,961
this wasn't here when we left, right?

1697
01:04:55,961 --> 01:04:58,743
Yes, these are basically
our household belongings.

1698
01:04:58,743 --> 01:05:00,552
Shall we take them out one by one?

1699
01:05:00,552 --> 01:05:03,680
- Sorry, but isn't this a trash bag?
- Ah, no, no.

1700
01:05:03,680 --> 01:05:04,681
First of all...

1701
01:05:04,681 --> 01:05:06,095
[Item 1, Strawberry Milk]
Strawberry Milk!

1702
01:05:06,095 --> 01:05:08,193
- What is it?
- This belongs to Yumi...

1703
01:05:08,193 --> 01:05:09,983
- she didn't drink it yesterday.
- I didn't drink it yesterday.

1704
01:05:09,983 --> 01:05:11,356
- Ah...
- Just in case.

1705
01:05:11,356 --> 01:05:12,767
- You saved it?
- Yeah.

1706
01:05:12,767 --> 01:05:14,845
- We can't just throw anything away.
- Yeah.

1707
01:05:14,845 --> 01:05:18,831
This is the strawberry milk that Yumi
carefully carried all the way back to Seoul.

1708
01:05:18,831 --> 01:05:19,917
What else?

1709
01:05:19,917 --> 01:05:20,970
[Item 2, 500mL Bottled Water]

1710
01:05:20,970 --> 01:05:22,624
And... water.

1711
01:05:22,624 --> 01:05:25,418
It's water, but only half of it is left.
What kind of water is this?

1712
01:05:25,418 --> 01:05:29,122
It's still in progress.
We're still drinking it.

1713
01:05:29,122 --> 01:05:31,357
But why is there only one bottle of water?

1714
01:05:31,357 --> 01:05:33,564
- Because we mostly shared it.
- I see.

1715
01:05:33,564 --> 01:05:35,161
[The days they survived
on a single bottle of water]

1716
01:05:35,161 --> 01:05:37,401
There were lots of times
when we didn't have water...

1717
01:05:37,401 --> 01:05:38,564
- just in case.
- Just in case.

1718
01:05:38,564 --> 01:05:41,154
Well, you need water to survive, just in case.

1719
01:05:41,154 --> 01:05:43,116
In case something happens, so...

1720
01:05:43,116 --> 01:05:45,800
They've already drunk about two-thirds of it.

1721
01:05:45,800 --> 01:05:48,514
They made it all the way to Seoul
with one-third left.

1722
01:05:50,874 --> 01:05:52,677
[Item 3, An Unknown Lump]

1723
01:05:52,677 --> 01:05:54,112
Well, this is...

1724
01:05:54,112 --> 01:05:56,563
- What is this?
- I'm sure you're very curious.

1725
01:05:56,563 --> 01:05:58,053
Try guessing what it is, yes.

1726
01:05:58,053 --> 01:06:00,395
- Take a guess.
- Yeah, take a guess.

1727
01:06:00,395 --> 01:06:03,050
- What matters is the type of bread.
- Looks like bread.

1728
01:06:03,050 --> 01:06:04,219
[Is it jerky? A rotten mushroom?]

1729
01:06:04,219 --> 01:06:07,047
Well, it's a leftover piece of bread.

1730
01:06:07,047 --> 01:06:09,980
But honestly, they've already eaten so much.

1731
01:06:09,980 --> 01:06:12,889
Wouldn't most people throw this away
if only one bite was left?

1732
01:06:12,889 --> 01:06:14,721
- Ah, but just in case...
- Just in case.

1733
01:06:14,721 --> 01:06:18,676
In case we got a little hungry and
ended up making unnecessary purchases.

1734
01:06:18,676 --> 01:06:20,585
So they're saving it
and eating it little by little.

1735
01:06:20,585 --> 01:06:22,867
Now then, if there's anything else
to show from the other bag.

1736
01:06:22,867 --> 01:06:26,205
- Well, I'm not sure if I can show this.
- What is it?

1737
01:06:26,205 --> 01:06:27,613
- Huh?
- Huh?

1738
01:06:27,613 --> 01:06:28,920
We've really been saving this.

1739
01:06:28,920 --> 01:06:32,837
- Oh, we bought that there, right?
- Show us.

1740
01:06:32,837 --> 01:06:34,996
[More food]

1741
01:06:34,996 --> 01:06:37,840
[This bag is also full of emergency rations]
- Well, this is S***. - Yes.

1742
01:06:37,840 --> 01:06:39,746
[There's more]

1743
01:06:39,746 --> 01:06:42,945
And one pack of An***Tang Myeon ramyeon.

1744
01:06:42,945 --> 01:06:45,420
Ah, and this is a little too personal...
is this okay to show?

1745
01:06:45,420 --> 01:06:47,951
Seo Jun, is it okay if I reveal this?

1746
01:06:47,951 --> 01:06:52,116
- There are even hairs stuck to it.
- This one is Woo Shik's.

1747
01:06:52,116 --> 01:06:54,287
- Please show it.
- Is it okay if I show this?

1748
01:06:54,287 --> 01:06:57,094
- Well, whatever's inside.
- But was it originally this color?

1749
01:06:58,914 --> 01:07:00,235
[Boldly revealing a private item]
Ta-da!

1750
01:07:00,235 --> 01:07:03,227
Yes, they're pajamas. Not a hospital gown.

1751
01:07:03,227 --> 01:07:06,299
And next, this is something
I've really been saving.

1752
01:07:06,299 --> 01:07:08,315
We haven't even opened it yet.

1753
01:07:08,315 --> 01:07:10,160
[An unopened chewy candy]

1754
01:07:10,160 --> 01:07:12,907
Actually, we didn't buy this.

1755
01:07:12,907 --> 01:07:18,374
We found a student's phone
while we were traveling somewhere,

1756
01:07:18,374 --> 01:07:20,322
and they bought us this precious gift

1757
01:07:20,322 --> 01:07:21,652
- and gave it to us.
- Chewy candy.

1758
01:07:21,652 --> 01:07:25,533
[Day 3 of the trip, Boseong Yulpo Beach]
Excuse me! Is this perhaps...

1759
01:07:25,533 --> 01:07:28,626
Huh? Oh! Hey, this is your phone!

1760
01:07:29,542 --> 01:07:31,519
Thank you!

1761
01:07:32,378 --> 01:07:34,205
[The students they happened
to meet at the beach]

1762
01:07:34,205 --> 01:07:37,871
They were so grateful that
they gave us this as a gift.

1763
01:07:37,871 --> 01:07:40,259
- Because they were so thankful.
- Chewy candy?

1764
01:07:40,259 --> 01:07:43,055
This is only one bag now,
but they actually gave us two.

1765
01:07:43,055 --> 01:07:44,602
- You already ate one.
- Yeah.

1766
01:07:44,602 --> 01:07:48,202
- This one still hasn't been opened.
- Yes, we don't even plan on opening it.

1767
01:07:48,202 --> 01:07:50,471
[Will be preserved forever out of gratitude]

1768
01:07:50,471 --> 01:07:53,362
Well, this was the kind of trip
that left them with things like these.

1769
01:07:53,362 --> 01:07:56,973
I think it'd be nice to see how they
ended up collecting all these things.

1770
01:07:56,973 --> 01:07:59,474
If there's anything memorable from the trip,

1771
01:07:59,474 --> 01:08:02,360
please share a few words.

1772
01:08:02,360 --> 01:08:04,606
Yumi, what stands out in your memory?

1773
01:08:04,606 --> 01:08:06,821
Every day, every moment.

1774
01:08:06,821 --> 01:08:08,961
Honestly, I can't remember.

1775
01:08:09,607 --> 01:08:12,784
I think I'll have to watch the broadcast
to remember it myself.

1776
01:08:12,784 --> 01:08:17,023
[Asked once again]
Still, there must be a few memorable moments.

1777
01:08:17,023 --> 01:08:22,644
I feel like I've met and seen
so many different people.

1778
01:08:23,241 --> 01:08:25,644
That was good.

1779
01:08:25,644 --> 01:08:27,845
The person I remember most right now is

1780
01:08:27,845 --> 01:08:31,266
the man who gave us bread.

1781
01:08:31,266 --> 01:08:33,794
Compare it to that 60-year-old
bread from Daejeon.

1782
01:08:33,794 --> 01:08:35,879
- Can we really accept this?
- Yeah, go ahead and eat it.

1783
01:08:35,879 --> 01:08:37,539
That bread must be
over a hundred years old by now.

1784
01:08:37,539 --> 01:08:38,740
Wow.

1785
01:08:38,740 --> 01:08:41,826
And then the grandmother
who ran the lodging in Boseong.

1786
01:08:41,826 --> 01:08:43,257
- With the key in hand.
- Yes.

1787
01:08:43,257 --> 01:08:45,284
[The kind grandma from a Boseong guesthouse]
I know you. I've seen you on TV a lot.

1788
01:08:45,284 --> 01:08:48,258
Oh my, hello. Hello.

1789
01:08:48,258 --> 01:08:52,263
And then the next day,
we went out for breakfast, right?

1790
01:08:52,263 --> 01:08:55,789
The owner who made us the soybean paste stew.

1791
01:08:55,789 --> 01:08:58,633
And she even gave us
sweet potatoes when we left.

1792
01:08:58,633 --> 01:09:02,654
And she handed me a mugwort pancake,
saying, "Spring has arrived."

1793
01:09:02,654 --> 01:09:05,638
She really stayed in my memory.

1794
01:09:05,638 --> 01:09:07,958
[People who showed selfless kindness]
I'm okay. Thank you.

1795
01:09:07,958 --> 01:09:09,879
Thank you.

1796
01:09:09,879 --> 01:09:12,168
[Their warmth made the journey special]
Can I accept this?

1797
01:09:12,168 --> 01:09:13,447
Really?

1798
01:09:13,447 --> 01:09:14,911
Oh, thank you.

1799
01:09:14,911 --> 01:09:19,879
As we traveled around, there were just
so many people we were grateful to.

1800
01:09:19,879 --> 01:09:22,479
I think that's what stays with me the most.

1801
01:09:22,479 --> 01:09:24,105
And Seo Jun too.

1802
01:09:24,105 --> 01:09:25,319
Well, for me...

1803
01:09:25,319 --> 01:09:26,545
[What Seo Jun felt during this trip...]

1804
01:09:26,545 --> 01:09:31,325
Honestly, I got to visit some places
I'd always wanted to see.

1805
01:09:31,325 --> 01:09:33,239
Normally,

1806
01:09:33,239 --> 01:09:36,778
those kinds of distances that I'd never
easily commit to traveling...

1807
01:09:36,778 --> 01:09:38,832
- Right.
- Taking public transportation,

1808
01:09:38,832 --> 01:09:42,212
seeing the scenery along the way,

1809
01:09:42,212 --> 01:09:44,193
All of that made me...

1810
01:09:44,193 --> 01:09:47,384
feel like I was back in my college days.

1811
01:09:47,384 --> 01:09:50,370
- Right, right. Like when we were students.
- Yeah.

1812
01:09:50,370 --> 01:09:53,585
Traveling like this every single day,

1813
01:09:53,585 --> 01:09:57,189
I think it was my first time doing that.

1814
01:09:57,189 --> 01:09:59,847
We were moving around like this every day.

1815
01:09:59,847 --> 01:10:03,563
This is the first time in my life
I've traveled like this.

1816
01:10:03,563 --> 01:10:06,320
Of course, there were times I slept
because I was so exhausted.

1817
01:10:06,320 --> 01:10:10,330
[Under the difficult condition
of having to move every day]

1818
01:10:11,295 --> 01:10:14,678
The plans may have been a complete mess,

1819
01:10:14,678 --> 01:10:18,110
but there was fun in figuring
things out along the way.

1820
01:10:18,110 --> 01:10:23,234
So rather than staring at my phone,
I talk with people around me

1821
01:10:23,234 --> 01:10:25,129
and spend time thinking.

1822
01:10:25,129 --> 01:10:27,711
But you know you can put this
on your face too, right?

1823
01:10:27,711 --> 01:10:29,202
But that's lip balm.

1824
01:10:29,202 --> 01:10:31,155
Really? Then I'm gonna use it.

1825
01:10:31,155 --> 01:10:35,711
[Being together with the friends beside me]

1826
01:10:35,711 --> 01:10:38,723
[In this very moment]

1827
01:10:38,723 --> 01:10:41,100
- It's the lodging.
- Huh? Looks like the character for "so..."

1828
01:10:41,100 --> 01:10:42,744
No way...

1829
01:10:42,744 --> 01:10:48,497
[The restrictions made them
appreciate ordinary days even more]

1830
01:10:49,208 --> 01:10:53,435
[Not in the past or future,
but in the present moment]

1831
01:10:53,435 --> 01:10:54,584
[#Heading to Jeju from Wando]

1832
01:10:54,584 --> 01:10:56,359
[Fully taking in the scenery before them]

1833
01:10:56,359 --> 01:10:58,848
Huh? That man is giving it to them.

1834
01:10:58,848 --> 01:11:01,825
[A youthful trip filled
with laughter and conversation]

1835
01:11:01,825 --> 01:11:03,266
Personally,

1836
01:11:03,266 --> 01:11:06,473
while taking this 5-night, 6-day journey,

1837
01:11:06,473 --> 01:11:10,033
[A limited trip that seemed impossible]
It gave me confidence, and made me realize that

1838
01:11:10,033 --> 01:11:15,111
things I once thought were impossible might

1839
01:11:15,111 --> 01:11:18,050
actually be possible for me.

1840
01:11:18,050 --> 01:11:20,065
When you go through hardships together,

1841
01:11:20,065 --> 01:11:25,163
everything becomes more fun,
and food tastes better too.

1842
01:11:25,163 --> 01:11:27,007
They were all brief moments,

1843
01:11:27,007 --> 01:11:30,746
but I think they'll remain as great
and fun memories.

1844
01:11:30,746 --> 01:11:34,055
I think it was a truly unique trip.

1845
01:11:34,055 --> 01:11:37,655
I think it was a trip
I'll never be able to experience again.

1846
01:11:40,951 --> 01:11:41,993
Youth Over...

1847
01:11:41,993 --> 01:11:44,333
- Flowers!
- Flowers!

1848
01:11:46,422 --> 01:11:49,450
Alright. Since this question came up,
let me ask just one thing.

1849
01:11:49,450 --> 01:11:52,543
Lastly, if you were to take
another trip in this exact format

1850
01:11:52,543 --> 01:11:56,275
with the same members, would you go?

1851
01:11:56,275 --> 01:11:58,328
Domestic or overseas?

1852
01:11:59,148 --> 01:12:00,770
Already asking about the conditions.

1853
01:12:00,770 --> 01:12:01,886
[A practical question
that naturally requires conditions...]

1854
01:12:01,886 --> 01:12:03,964
Well, the answer to that question...

1855
01:12:03,964 --> 01:12:06,899
please stay tuned until the end
of the broadcast to find out.

1856
01:12:06,899 --> 01:12:08,788
We'll wrap up today's broadcast here.

1857
01:12:08,788 --> 01:12:10,479
- Thank you.
- Everyone, we made it back safely.

1858
01:12:10,479 --> 01:12:12,601
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

1859
01:12:12,601 --> 01:12:13,685
Thank you!

1860
01:12:13,685 --> 01:12:15,800
[Return livestream ends]

1861
01:12:15,800 --> 01:12:17,705
If it's the same three members

1862
01:12:17,705 --> 01:12:20,992
and a trip like this again,

1863
01:12:20,992 --> 01:12:22,023
would you go?

1864
01:12:22,023 --> 01:12:23,805
Oh, absolutely.

1865
01:12:25,004 --> 01:12:28,090
Ah, but I wonder what Choi Woo Shik will say.

1866
01:12:28,090 --> 01:12:31,243
[The youngest is in too]
For one, I want to go again.

1867
01:12:31,243 --> 01:12:33,579
[Lastly, Yumi's choice is...]
- Would you go? - When?

1868
01:12:33,579 --> 01:12:36,784
- Anytime.
- I don't think I could do it in a few years.

1869
01:12:36,784 --> 01:12:40,246
My heart is young, but my body right now...

1870
01:12:40,246 --> 01:12:42,046
If I had to go,

1871
01:12:42,046 --> 01:12:45,937
it would have to be with these
same members and the same staff.

1872
01:12:45,937 --> 01:12:49,043
[Yumi also gives conditional approval!]
Otherwise, I think I'd be too shocked.

1873
01:12:49,710 --> 01:12:50,734
[And]

1874
01:12:50,734 --> 01:12:52,741
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

1875
01:12:52,741 --> 01:12:54,874
- Thank you.
- Yep, it's over.

1876
01:12:54,874 --> 01:12:56,544
- Thank you.
- Here, your phones.

1877
01:12:56,544 --> 01:12:58,695
[The Limited restrictions are finally lifted]
Our phones.

1878
01:12:58,695 --> 01:12:59,710
Come on, come on.

1879
01:12:59,710 --> 01:13:02,063
[Time to return to everyday life]
- Wow! - Is this Woo Shik's?

1880
01:13:02,063 --> 01:13:03,820
Whose...

1881
01:13:03,820 --> 01:13:05,393
Oh, and there's one more thing.

1882
01:13:05,393 --> 01:13:08,251
- Since you all successfully finished the trip,
- Yes.

1883
01:13:08,251 --> 01:13:10,751
- Oh, there's a gift?
- Benefit?

1884
01:13:10,751 --> 01:13:13,093
[The three react right away to "benefit"]
- Benefit? - Not a benefit, but...

1885
01:13:13,093 --> 01:13:15,084
Since you seemed to use
the camcorder really well,

1886
01:13:15,084 --> 01:13:16,717
- we got each of you the same model camcorder.
- Wow!

1887
01:13:16,717 --> 01:13:19,257
- Thank you.
- Really?

1888
01:13:19,257 --> 01:13:21,577
Woo Shik was actually planning to buy this.

1889
01:13:21,577 --> 01:13:22,765
That's awesome.

1890
01:13:22,765 --> 01:13:24,197
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1891
01:13:24,197 --> 01:13:26,193
- This is it.
- You used it so well the whole time.

1892
01:13:26,193 --> 01:13:30,184
- Wow, I was really going to buy this.
- Yeah, you said you were going to.

1893
01:13:30,184 --> 01:13:32,246
[And Treasurer Park too]
I'm really going to use this well.

1894
01:13:32,246 --> 01:13:35,736
[Time to head home]
- Thank you. Good work. - Good work.

1895
01:13:35,736 --> 01:13:39,486
Lastly, what's the first thing you want to do
when you get home today?

1896
01:13:39,486 --> 01:13:43,843
First, put everything I'm wearing
into the laundry basket...

1897
01:13:43,843 --> 01:13:46,785
I feel like I need to throw
these clothes away first.

1898
01:13:46,785 --> 01:13:48,328
[The outfit they've had enough of]

1899
01:13:48,328 --> 01:13:50,357
Do some laundry.

1900
01:13:50,357 --> 01:13:52,499
Seriously, I'm not even kidding.

1901
01:13:52,499 --> 01:13:55,536
When I get home, I'll sit on the couch

1902
01:13:55,536 --> 01:13:58,365
and zone out for about 30 minutes.

1903
01:13:58,365 --> 01:14:02,543
As I think through our journey
step by step from Daegu,

1904
01:14:02,543 --> 01:14:05,203
I think I'll spend some time by myself.

1905
01:14:05,203 --> 01:14:09,594
Because for the past 120 hours,

1906
01:14:09,594 --> 01:14:13,095
I haven't been alone even once.

1907
01:14:14,223 --> 01:14:17,947
So I think having some time for myself

1908
01:14:17,947 --> 01:14:20,834
might actually be good for me.

1909
01:14:21,480 --> 01:14:23,394
But it was such a wonderful memory.

1910
01:14:23,394 --> 01:14:25,456
[Wrapping up]

1911
01:14:26,630 --> 01:14:29,762
[The interview filming is now finished too]
- Great work. - Great work.

1912
01:14:30,600 --> 01:14:32,774
Wow, we really...

1913
01:14:32,774 --> 01:14:34,234
That was long.

1914
01:14:34,234 --> 01:14:35,458
Today was really long.

1915
01:14:35,458 --> 01:14:36,751
One, two, three.

1916
01:14:36,751 --> 01:14:38,005
[Unplanned Trip: Limited Edition]
Thank you!

1917
01:14:38,005 --> 01:14:39,185
[The real end!]
See you next time.

1918
01:14:39,185 --> 01:14:41,058
- Good work, everyone.
- Yes.
